(C) aism-0000000.description: (C): The projection of the inner surface of the cuticle.

(C) aism-0000174.description: (C): The insect region of integument that is part of the chitin-based cuticle.

(C) pato-0001857.description: (C): A shape quality in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's curving inward.

(C) aism-0000002.description: (C): The region of cuticle that is composed two articular surfaces that are adjacent to each other.

(C) aism-0000167.description: (C): The region of cuticle where two sclerites meet.

(C) aism-0000003.description: (C): The region of the insect cuticle that is less flexible than the neighboring conjunctiva(e) (conjunctiva(e) that the sclerite is continuous with.

(C) aism-0000004.description: (C): The region of the insect cuticle that is more flexible than the neighboring sclerite(s) [sclerite(s) that the conjunctiva is continuous with].

(C) aism-0000005.description: (C): The region of the cuticle that corresponds to a concave surface.

(C) bspo-0000062.description: (C): Anatomical side that is distally located on an organism or structure.

(C) aism-0000006.description: (C): The region of cuticle that corresponds with an invagination of the single layer epidermis (epidermal fold). The cuticular invagination sometimes corresponds to a cuticular depression (concavity on the surface of the cuticle).

(C) aism-0000007.description: (C): The region of cuticle with higher content of resilin.

(C) aism-0000008.description: (C): The region of the cuticle that corresponds to a convex surface.

(C) pato-0001355.description: (C): A shape quality that obtains by virtue of the bearer having inward facing edges; having a surface or boundary that curves or bulges outward, as the exterior of a sphere.

(C) aism-0000013.description: (C): A part or structure that is produced by evagination.

(C) aism-0000014.description: (C): The articulation between the mandible and the cranium.

(C) aism-0000019.description: (C): The sclerite of the insect head that is attached to the neck membrane and the oral foraminal conjunctiva, bears the eye cuticle and surrounds the brain

(C) bspo-0000070.description: (C): A 3D region in space without well-defined compartmental boundaries; for example, the dorsal region of an ectoderm.

(C) aism-0000043.description: (C): The cuticle of the mouthpart and sclerite between the cuticle of the labrum and the cuticle of the insect maxilla that is attached to the head capsule by the oral foraminal conjunctiva and the cranio-mandibular muscle.

(C) aism-0000015.description: (C): The articulation between the cardo and the cranium.

(C) aism-0000018.description: (C): The sclerite of the insect maxilla that is attached to the head capsule by the oral foraminal conjunctiva and to the cuticle of stipes by the stipito-cardinal conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0000016.description: (C): The articulation between the scapus and the cranium.

(C) aism-0000113.description: (C): The cuticle of the segment of the antenna that is connected to the head capsule and the antennifer by the basal antennal conjunctiva and to the pedicellus by the scapal-pedicellar conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0000017.description: (C): The articulation between the head and the neck.

(C) aism-0000098.description: (C): The conjuctiva that is continuous with the posterior margin of the head capsule and with the anterior margin of the prothorax, and bears cervical sclerites.

(C) aism-0000044.description: (C): The cuticle of the mouthpart appendage of the head capsule, between the cuticle of the insect mandible and the cuticle of the labium, composed of cuticle of cardo, which is attached to the cuticle of stipes by the cardo-stipital conjunctiva; the cuticle of stipes, which is attached to the cuticle of galea by the stipito-galeal conjunctiva, to the cuticle of lacinia by the stipito-lacinial conjunctiva, and to the cuticle of palpifer by the stipito-palpiferal conjunctiva; the cuticle of palpifer is attached to the cuticle of maxillary palpus by the palpifero-palpal conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0000099.description: (C): The conjunctiva of the insect head that connects the head capsule and the mouthparts.

(C) aism-0000110.description: (C): The conjunctiva of the insect maxilla that connects the cardo and the stipes.

(C) aism-0000111.description: (C): The cuticle of the sclerite of the insect maxilla that is attached to the cuticle of cardo by the cardo-stipital conjunctiva, attached to the cuticle of lacinia by the stipito-lacinial conjunctiva, attached to the cuticle of palpifer by the stipito-palpiferal conjunctiva, and attached to the cuticle of galea by the stipito-galeal conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0000107.description: (C): The cuticular region that is anterior (distal) to the neck membrane (encircled by the neck membrane) and contains the head capsule, the antenna, the eyes, mouthparts and surrounds the brain.

(C) aism-0000088.description: (C): The elastic cuticle of the head capsule that is transparent and covers the eye.

(C) aism-0000020.description: (C): The axillary sclerite that is on the dorsal region of the basal wing conjunctiva and lateral to the first axillary sclerite.

(C) aism-0004161.description: (C): The sclerite that is surrounded by the basal wing conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0000022.description: (C): The axillary sclerite that is part of the dorsal region of the basal wing conjunctiva and is anterior to the third axillary sclerite.

(C) bspo-0000079.description: (C): Anatomical region dorsally located on the body or body part.

(C) aism-0004203.description: (C): The conjunctiva of the pterothorax that surrounds the wing.

(C) aism-0000021.description: (C): Is the abdominal tergite of the preabdomen that is attached to the posterior margin of the tergum by the metanoto-abdominal tergite I conjunctiva and to the anterior margin of the abdominal tergite II by the abdominal tergite I-abdominal tergite II conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0004057.description: (C): The sclerite of the insect abdomen that is dorsal and medial.

(C) aism-0004055.description: (C): The region of cuticle of the insect abdomen that is posteriorly connected to the postabdomen.

(C) bspo-0000671.description: (C): Anatomical margin that is located on the anterior side of a body or body part.

(C) aism-0004085.description: (C): Is the abdominal tergite of the preabdomen that is attached to the posterior margin of the abdominal tergite I by the abdominal tergite I-abdominal tergite II conjunctiva and to the anterior margin of the abdominal tergite III by the abdominal tergite II-abdominal tergite III conjunctiva.

(C) bspo-0000672.description: (C): Anatomical margin that is located on the posterior side of the body or body part.

(C) aism-0000169.description: (C): The notum or sclerite on the dorsal region of the metathorax that is posterior to the mesonotum, connected via the metanoto-metapleural conjuntiva to the dorsal margin of the metapleuron, that is not adjacent to the metacoxa, but attached to it by the metacoxal muscle.

(C) aism-0004082.description: (C): The conjunctiva between the insect thorax and the insect abdomen that connects the posterior margin of the metanotum to the anterior margin of the abdominal tergite I.

(C) aism-0004086.description: (C): The conjunctiva of the insect abdomen that connects the abdominal tergite I and the abdominal tergite II.
(C) aism-0004086.label_original: abdominal tergite I-abdominal tergite II conjunctiva

(C) aism-0004223.description: (C): The axillary sclerite that is connected via muscle to the mesopleuron and is  posterior to the first axillary sclerite.

(C) aism-0000023.description: (C): The cuticle of the appendage of the insect maxilla that is attached to the stipes by the stipito-galeal conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0000029.description: (C): The evagination of the cuticle that is musculated (connected to the body via muscles).

(C) aism-0004011.description: (C): The conjunctiva of the insect maxilla that connects the stipes and the galea.

(C) aism-0000024.description: (C): The cuticle of the paired appendage of the labium that is attached to the palpiger by the palpigero-palpal conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0004017.description: (C): The conjunctiva of the labium that connects the palpiger and the labial palpus.

(C) aism-0000087.description: (C): The cuticle of the mouthpart appendage composed of the cuticle of submentum, which is attached by the submental-mental conjunctiva to the cuticle of mentum, which is attached by the mental-premental conjunctiva to the cuticle of prementum, which is attached to the cuticle of palpiger by the premental-palpigeral conjunctiva, the cuticle of paraglossa by the premental-paraglossal conjunctiva, and the cuticle of glossa by the premental-glossal conjunctiva; the cuticle of palpiger is attached by the palpigero-palpal conjunctiva to the cuticle of labial palpus.

(C) pato-0040024.description: (C): The bearer of this quality has_part n=2 of the indicated entity type, where n is unpaired for a comparable organism.

(C) aism-0004006.description: (C): The sclerite of the cuticle of labium that is attached to the prementum by the premental-palpigeral conjunctiva and to the cuticle of labial palpus by the palpigero-palpal conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0000026.description: (C): The cuticle of the appendage of the insect maxilla that is attached to the cuticle of stipes by the stipito-lacinial conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0004009.description: (C): The conjunctiva of the insect maxilla that connects the stipes and the lacinia.

(C) aism-0000027.description: (C): The region of cuticle that corresponds with an evagination of the cuticle and the single layer epidermis (epidermal fold). The cuticular evagination usually corresponds to a cuticular protrusion (convexity on the surface of the cuticle).

(C) aism-0000028.description: (C): The cuticular protrusion that does not correspond to an evagination.

(C) aism-0000128.description: (C): The region of cuticle that corresponds to the evagination of the single layer epithelium.

(C) aism-0000031.description: (C): The cuticle of the paired appendage of the insect thorax that is composed of coxa, trochanter, femur, tibia, tarsus, and pretarsus.

(C) aism-0000108.description: (C): The region of cuticle that is connected to some muscles of the fore and hind legs and is posterior to the neck membrane and aterior to the first abdominal spiracle.

(C) aism-0000047.description: (C): The cuticle of the appendage of the insect leg that is attached to the cuticle of tarsus by the tarso-pretarsal conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0000075.description: (C): The cuticle of the segment of a leg attached to the distal margin of the femur by the femoro-tibial conjunctiva and to the proximal margin of the tarsus by the tibio-tarsal conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0000076.description: (C): The cuticle of the segment of a leg attached to the distal margin of the trochanter by the trochantero-femoral conjunctiva and to the proximal margin of the tibia by the femoro-tibial conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0000077.description: (C): The cuticle of the segment of the leg that is attached to the latero-ventral region of the insect thorax by the basal coxal conjunctiva and to the trochanter by the coxal-trochanteral conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0004168.description: (C): The cuticle of the segment of a leg attached to the distal margin of the coxa by the coxal-trochanteral conjunctiva and to the proximal margin of the femur by the trochantero-femoral conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0004169.description: (C): The cuticle of the segment of the leg that is composed of tarsomeres connected to each other by intertarsomeral conjunctiva. The first tarsomere is connected to the distal margin of the tibia by the tibio-tarsal conjunctiva and last tarsomere is connected to the proximal margin of the pretarsus by the tarso-pretarsal conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0000032.description: (C): The cuticle of the appendage of the head capsule that is connected by the  antenniferal-scapal conjunctiva to the cuticle of the scapus, which is connected by the scapal-pedicellar conjunctiva to the cuticle of the pedicellus; the cuticle of the pedicellus is connected by the pedicellar-first flagellomeral conjunctiva to the cuticle of the first flagellomere; the cuticle of the first flagellomere is connected by interflagellomeral conjunctiva to the next cuticle of flagellomere. Further cuticle of flagellomeres are connected to each other by interflagellomeral conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0004007.description: (C): The conjunctiva of the head capsule that connects the antennifer and the scapus.

(C) aism-0000114.description: (C): The conjunctiva of the antenna that connects the scapus and the pedicellus.

(C) aism-0000115.description: (C): The cuticle of the segment of the antenna that is attached to the scapus by the scapal-pedicellar conjunctiva and to the first flagellomere by the pedicel-first flagellomere conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0000117.description: (C): The cuticle of the first flagellomere of the antenna, attached to the pedicel by the pedicel-first flagellomere conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0000118.description: (C): The conjunctiva of the antenna that connects the pedicellus and the first flagellomere.

(C) aism-0004008.description: (C): Is the conjunctiva of the antenna that connects a flagellomere and other flagellomere.

(C) aism-0000033.description: (C): The cuticle of the flat, paired appendage on the dorso-lateral region of the pterothorax.

(C) bspo-0000080.description: (C): Anatomical region that overlaps the dorsal and lateral regions of a body or body part.

(C) aism-0004166.description: (C): The region of cuticle of the insect thorax that contains the mesothorax and the metathorax and bears the mid legs, the hind legs and the wings.

(C) pato-0000407.description: (C): A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having a horizontal surface without a slope, tilt, or curvature.

(C) aism-0000034.description: (C): The cuticle of the paired appendage of the prothorax that is anterior to the cuticle of a mid leg and composed of cuticle of procoxa, cuticle of protrochanter, cuticle of profemur, cuticle of protibia, cuticle of protarsus, and cuticle of propretarsus.

(C) aism-0004125.description: (C): The region of the cuticle of the insect thorax that is anteriorly connected to the head by the neck membrane, posteriorly connected to the mesothorax by the prothorax-mesothorax conjunctiva, and contains the pronotum, the propeluron, the prosternum and one pair of legs.

(C) aism-0000066.description: (C): The cuticle of the segment of the fore leg that is attached to the latero-ventral region of the prothorax by the basal procoxal conjunctiva and to the protrochanter by the procoxal-protrochanteral conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0000067.description: (C): The cuticle of the segment of a fore leg attached to the distal margin of the profemur by the profemoro-protibial conjunctiva and to the proximal margin of the protarsus by the protibio-protarsal conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0000070.description: (C): The cuticle of the segment of a fore leg attached to the distal margin of the protrochanter by the protrochantero-profemoral conjunctiva and to the proximal margin of the protibia by the profemoro-protibial conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0004171.description: (C): The cuticle of the segment of a fore leg attached to the distal margin of the procoxa by the procoxal-protrochanteral conjunctiva and to the proximal margin of the profemur by the protrochantero-profemoral conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0004190.description: (C): The cuticle of the segment of the leg that is composed of protarsomeres connected to each other by intertarsomeral conjunctiva. The first protarsomere is connected to the distal margin of the protibia by the protibio-protarsal conjunctiva and the last protarsomere is connected to the proximal margin of the propretarsus by the protarso-propretarsal conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0004194.description: (C): The cuticle of the appendage of the fore leg that is attached to the protarsus by the protarso-propretarsal conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0000035.description: (C): The cuticle of the paired appendage of the mesothorax that is posterior to the cuticle of a fore leg, anterior to the cuticle of a hind leg, and composed of cuticle of mesocoxa, cuticle of mesotrochanter, cuticle of mesofemur, cuticle of mesotibia, cuticle of mesotarsus, and cuticle of mesopretarsus.

(C) aism-0004126.description: (C): The region of the cuticle of the pterothorax that bears mid legs and fore wings.

(C) aism-0000064.description: (C): The cuticle of the segment of the mid leg that is attached to the latero-ventral region of the mesothorax by the basal mesocoxal conjunctiva and to the mesotrochanter by the mesocoxal-mesotrochanteral conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0000068.description: (C): The cuticle of the segment of a mid leg attached to the distal margin of the mesofemur by the mesofemoro-mesotibial conjunctiva and to the proximal margin of the mesotarsus by the mesotibio-mesotarsal conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0000071.description: (C): The cuticle of the segment of a mid leg attached to the distal margin of the mesotrochanter by the mesotrochantero-mesofemoral conjunctiva and to the proximal margin of the mesotibia by the mesofemoro-mesotibial conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0004172.description: (C): The cuticle of the segment of a mid leg attached to the distal margin of the mesocoxa by the mesocoxal-mesotrochanteral conjunctiva and to the proximal margin of the mesofemur by the mesotrochantero-mesofemoral conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0004189.description: (C): The cuticle of the segment of the mid leg that is composed of mesotarsomeres connected to each other by intertarsomeral conjunctiva. The first mesotarsomere is connected to the distal margin of the mesotibia by the mesotibio-mesotarsal conjunctiva and the last mesotarsomere is connected to the proximal margin of the mesopretarsus by the mesotarso-mesopretarsal conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0004195.description: (C): The cuticle of the appendage of the mid leg that is attached to the mesotarsus by the mesotarso-mesopretarsal conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0000036.description: (C): The cuticle of the paired appendage of the metathorax that is posterior to the cuticle of a mid leg and composed of cuticle of metacoxa, cuticle of metatrochanter, cuticle of metafemur, cuticle of metatibia, cuticle of metatarsus, and cuticle of metapretarsus.

(C) aism-0004127.description: (C): The region of the cuticle of the pterothorax that bears the hind legs and the hind wings.

(C) aism-0000065.description: (C): The cuticle of the segment of the hind leg that is attached to the latero-ventral region of the metathorax by the basal metacoxal conjunctiva and to the metatrochanter by the metacoxal-metatrochanteral conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0000069.description: (C): The cuticle of the segment of a hind leg attached to the distal margin of the metafemur by the metafemoro-metatibial conjunctiva and to the proximal margin of the metatarsus by the metatibio-metatarsal conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0000072.description: (C): The cuticle of the segment of a hind leg attached to the distal margin of the metatrochanter by the metatrochantero-metafemoral conjunctiva and to the proximal margin of the metatibia by the metafemoro-metatibial conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0004173.description: (C): The cuticle of the segment of a hind leg attached to the distal margin of the metacoxa by the metacoxal-metatrochanteral conjunctiva and to the proximal margin of the metafemur by the metatrochantero-metafemoral conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0004188.description: (C): The cuticle of the segment of the leg that is composed of metatarsomeres connected to each other by intertarsomeral conjunctiva. The first metatarsomere is connected to the distal margin of the metatibia by the metatibio-metatarsal conjunctiva and the last metatarsomere is connected to the proximal margin of the metapretarsus by the metatarso-metapretarsal conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0004196.description: (C): The cuticle of the appendage of the hind leg that is attached to the metatarsus by the metatarso-metapretarsal conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0000037.description: (C): The cuticle of the paired insect wing that is continuous with the mesonotum.

(C) aism-0000052.description: (C): The notum or sclerite on the dorsal region of the mesothorax that is posterior to the pronotum, connected via the mesonoto-mesopleural conjuntiva to the dorsal margin of the mesopleuron, that is not adjacent to the mesocoxa, but attached to it by the mesocoxal muscle.

(C) aism-0000038.description: (C): The cuticle of the paired insect wing that is continuous with the metanotum.

(C) aism-0000039.description: (C): The unicellular cuticular evagination that constitutes a sclerite with its base surrounded by socket membrane.

(C) aism-0000127.description: (C): The cuticular evagination that corresponds to the evagination on the membrane of a single cell and not to the evagination of a cell layer.

(C) aism-0000126.description: (C): The conjunctiva that corresponds to one epithelial cell and surrounds a sclerotized unicellular cuticular evagination.

(C) aism-0000040.description: (C): The multicellular evagination of the cuticle that corresponds to an epithelial fold, composed of some sclerite that is encricled by a conjunctiva (moveable).

(C) pato-0002254.description: (C): A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's surface becoming more extended in a plane.

(C) aism-0000042.description: (C): The cuticle of the mouthpart and appendage that is attached to the clypeus by the clypeo-labral conjunctiva and to the proximal margin of the epipharynx.

(C) aism-0000165.description: (C): The cuticle of the appendage of the insect head that is encircled by the oral foraminal conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0004018.description: (C): The conjunctiva of the insect maxilla that connects the clypeus and the labrum.

(C) bspo-0000677.description: (C): Anatomical margin that is located on the proximal region of the body or body part.

(C) aism-0000105.description: (C): The conjunctiva of the insect head that is connected to the oral foraminal conjunctiva and to the distal margin of the labrum.

(C) aism-0004019.description: (C): The region of the head capsule that is anterior to the frons and is attached to the labrum by the clypeo-labral conjunctiva

(C) aism-0000082.description: (C): The somatic muscle that is attached to the head capsule and the insect mandible.

(C) aism-0000051.description: (C): The cuticle of the appendage of the insect maxilla that is attached to the cuticle of palpifer by the palpifero-palpal conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0004001.description: (C): The sclerite of the insect maxilla that is attached to the cuticle of stipes by the stipito-palpiferal conjunctiva and to the cuticle of maxillary palpus by the palpifero-palpal conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0004010.description: (C): The conjunctiva of the insect maxilla that connects the stipes and the palpifer.

(C) aism-0004012.description: (C): The conjunctiva of the insect maxilla that connects the palpifer and the maxillary palpus.

(C) aism-0000045.description: (C): The conjunctiva of the insect thorax that connects the mesothorax and the metathorax.

(C) aism-0000046.description: (C): The conjunctiva of the insect thorax joining the prothorax and the mesothorax.

(C) aism-0004187.description: (C): The conjunctiva that encircles the pretarsus by joining the distal margin of the distalmost tarsomere and the proximal margin of the pretarsus.

(C) bspo-0000678.description: (C): Anatomical margin that is located on the distal side of the body or body part.

(C) aism-0000048.description: (C): The cuticle of the appendage of the cuticle of labium composed of the cuticle of glossa and cuticle of paraglossa jointly.

(C) aism-0000049.description: (C): The cuticle of the appendage of the labium, and part of the ligula, that is attached to the prementum by the premental-glossal conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0000050.description: (C): The cuticle of the paired appendage of the labium, and part of the ligula, that is attached to the cuticle of prementum by the premental-paraglossal conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0004016.description: (C): The conjunctiva of the labium that connects the prementum and the glossa.

(C) aism-0000057.description: (C): The sclerite of the labium that is connected to the mentum by the mental-premental conjunctiva, to the palpiger by the premental-palpigeral conjunctiva, to the paraglossa by the premental-paraglossal conjunctiva, and to the glossa by the premental-glossal conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0004015.description: (C): The conjunctiva of the labium that connects the prementum and the paraglossa.

(C) aism-0004128.description: (C): The dorsal region of the cuticle of the insect thorax that is attached to the dorsal margin of the pleuron.

(C) aism-0000059.description: (C): The notum or sclerite on the dorsal region of the prothorax that is attached to cranial muscles, procoxal muscles, contiuous posterioirly with the neck membrane and with pronoto-propleural conjunctiva and not adjacent (not touching) to the procoxa.

(C) aism-0004219.description: (C): The noto-pleural conjunctiva that joins the mesonotum and the mesopleuron.

(C) bspo-0000679.description: (C): Anatomical margin that is located on the dorsal side of body or body part.

(C) aism-0004186.description: (C): The region of the cuticle on the lateral region of the mesothorax that is attached to the mesonotum and the mesosternum, and is attached to the mesocoxa by the mesocoxal muscle and the basal mesocoxal conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0000085.description: (C): The coxal muscle of the mesocoxa.

(C) aism-0000053.description: (C): The sclerite that is continuous with the basal mesocoxal conjunctiva and the basal wing conjunctiva and contains the mesofurca.

(C) aism-0000141.description: (C): The furca of the mesothorax that is attached to the mesocoxa via muscle.

(C) aism-0000103.description: (C): The conjunctiva that encircles the mesocoxa and connects it to the ventral and lateral regions of the mesothorax.

(C) aism-0000054.description: (C): The trochantin that is located on the ventro-lateral region of the mesothorax and is attached to a mesocoxa and surrounded by the basal mesocoxal conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0004135.description: (C): The sclerite that is located on the ventro-lateral region of the insect thorax and is attached to a coxa.

(C) bspo-0000085.description: (C): Anatomical region that overlaps the ventral and lateral regions of a body or body part.

(C) aism-0000055.description: (C): The trochantin that is located on the ventro-lateral region of the prothorax and is attached to a procoxa and surrounded by the basal procoxal conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0000106.description: (C): The conjunctiva that encircles the procoxa and connects it to the ventral and lateral regions of the prothorax.

(C) aism-0000056.description: (C): The trochantin that is located on the ventro-lateral region of the metathorax and is attached to a metacoxa and surrounded by the basal metacoxal conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0000104.description: (C): The conjunctiva that encircles the metacoxa and connects it to the ventral and lateral regions of the metathorax.

(C) aism-0004002.description: (C): The conjunctiva of the labium that connects the mentum and the prementum.

(C) aism-0004014.description: (C): The conjunctiva of the labium that connects the prementum and the palpiger.

(C) aism-0004004.description: (C): The sclerite of the labium that is anterior to the submentum and posterior to the prementum, and attached to the prementum by the mental-premental conjunctiva.

(C) aism-0000058.description: (C): The sclerite that is posterior to the pronotum and receives the site of attachment of the dilutor muscle of the first thoracic spiracle.

(C) aism-0000135.description: (C): The region of the cuticle that is continuous to the proximal region of a trachea and can be closed by muscles.

(C) aism-0004220.description: (C): The noto-pleural conjunctiva that joins the pronotum and the propleuron.

(OP) aism-0000011.description: (OP): X lateral to y if x is further from the midsagittal plane than y.

(OP) aism-0000012.description: (OP): X medial to y if x is closer to the midsagittal plane than y.

(OP) aism-0000078.description: (OP): x encircles y if both x and y are regions of the 2D structure z, or 2D cross-sections of a 3D object z, and the boundary of y on z is exclusively continuous with x.

(OP) ro-0002150.description: (OP): X continuous_with Y if and only if X and Y share a fiat boundary.

(OP) aism-0000079.description: (OP): y is encircled by x if both x and y are regions of the 2D structure z, or 2D cross-sections of a 3D object z, and the boundary of y on z is exclusively continuous with y.

(OP) bfo-0000050.description: (OP): a core relation that holds between a part and its whole

(OP) bfo-0000051.description: (OP): a core relation that holds between a whole and its part

(OP) bspo-0000096.description: (OP): x anterior to y iff x is further along the antero-posterior axis than y, towards the head. An antero-posterior axis is an axis that extends through an organism from head end to opposite end of body or tail.

(OP) bspo-0000099.description: (OP): x posterior to y iff x is further along the antero-posterior axis than y, towards the body/tail. An antero-posterior axis is an axis that extends through an organism from head end to opposite end of body or tail.

(OP) bspo-0000097.description: (OP): x distal to y iff x is further along the proximo-distal axis than y, towards the appendage tip. A proximo-distal axis extends from tip of an appendage (distal) to where it joins the body (proximal).

(OP) bspo-0000100.description: (OP): x proximal to y iff x is closer to the point of attachment with the body than y.

(OP) bspo-0000098.description: (OP): x dorsal to y iff x is further along the dorso-ventral axis than y, towards the back. A dorso-ventral axis is an axis that extends through an organism from back (e.g. spinal column) to front (e.g. belly).

(OP) bspo-0000102.description: (OP): x ventral to y iff x is further along the dorso-ventral axis than y, towards the front. A dorso-ventral axis is an axis that extends through an organism from back (e.g. spinal column) to front (e.g. belly).

(OP) ro-0000052.description: (OP): a relation between a specifically dependent continuant (the characteristic) and any other entity (the bearer), in which the characteristic depends on the bearer for its existence.

(OP) ro-0000086.description: (OP): a relation between an independent continuant (the bearer) and a quality, in which the quality specifically depends on the bearer for its existence

(OP) ro-0001015.description: (OP): a relation between two independent continuants, the location and the target, in which the target is entirely within the location

(OP) ro-0001025.description: (OP): a relation between two independent continuants, the target and the location, in which the target is entirely within the location

(OP) ro-0002008.description: (OP): A relation that holds between two linear structures that are approximately parallel to each other for their entire length and where either the two structures are adjacent to each other or one is part of the other.

(OP) ro-0002160.description: (OP): U only_in_taxon T: U is a feature found in only in organisms of species of taxon T. The feature cannot be found in an organism of any species outside of (not subsumed by) that taxon. Down-propagates in U hierarchy, up-propagates in T hierarchy (species taxonomy). Implies applicable_to_taxon.

(OP) ro-0002162.description: (OP): x is in taxon y if an only if y is an organism, and the relationship between x and y is one of: part of (reflexive), developmentally preceded by, derives from, secreted by, expressed.

(OP) ro-0002371.description: (OP): a is attached to b if and only if a and b are discrete objects or object parts, and there are physical connections between a and b such that a force pulling a will move b, or a force pulling b will move a

(OP) ro-0002220.description: (OP): x adjacent to y if and only if x and y share a boundary.

(OP) pato2-decreased_in_magnitude_relati.description: (OP): OBSOLETE. q1 decreased_in_magnitude_relative_to q2 if and only if magnitude(q1) < magnitude(q2). Here, magnitude(q) is a function that maps a quality to a unit-invariant scale.

(OP) pato2-increased_in_magnitude_relati.description: (OP): OBSOLETE. q1 increased_in_magnitude_relative_to q2 if and only if magnitude(q1) > magnitude(q2). Here, magnitude(q) is a function that maps a quality to a unit-invariant scale.

(AP) iao-0000700.description: (AP): Ontology annotation property. Relates an ontology to a term that is a designated root term of the ontology. Display tools like OLS can use terms annotated with this property as the starting point for rendering the ontology class hierarchy. There can be more than one root.

(AP) aism-0000171.description: (AP): This annotation property defines a 'sensu', which is the combination of a bibliographic reference, a label and a class (represented by verbatim and logical definitions). Given this model, independent observations can be inferred across to compute synonymy (multiple labels attached to one), homonymy (one label attached to multiple classes).    Yoder MJ, Mik I, Seltmann KC, Bertone MA, Deans AR (2010) A Gross Anatomy Ontology for Hymenoptera. PLOS ONE 5: e15991.      https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0015991.g004    This annotation property is on the label of a class in owl.

(AP) iao-0000115.description: (AP): The official definition, explaining the meaning of a class or property. Shall be Aristotelian, formalized and normalized. Can be augmented with colloquial definitions.

(AP) iao-0000232.description: (AP): An administrative note of use for a curator but of no use for a user

(AP) formats-hasExactSynonym.description: (AP): An alternative label for a class or property which has the exact same meaning than the preferred name/primary label.

(C) hao-0000613.description: (C): The pleural ridge that corresponds to the metapleural sulcus.

(C) hao-0000724.description: (C): The ridge that extends between the pleural wing process and the lateral coxal articulation and marks the border between the episternum and epimeron.

(C) hao-0000614.description: (C): The line that corresponds with the metapleural ridge.

(C) hao-0000725.description: (C): The sulcus that corresponds to the pleural ridge and separates the episternum from the epimeron.

(C) hao-0000615.description: (C): The area that is located anteroventrally on the metapectus, is delimited ventrally by the ventral carina of the metapleuron and is triangular.

(C) hao-0000616.description: (C): The metabasalar muscle that arises from the metapleuron and inserts on the metabasalare.

(C) hao-0000617.description: (C): The metanotal muscle that arises from the metapleuron and inserts on the metanotum.

(C) hao-0000618.description: (C): The metasubalare muscle that arises from the metapleuron and inserts on the metasubalare.

(C) hao-0000619.description: (C): The metatrochanteral muscle that arises from the metapleuron and inserts on the metatrochanteral apodeme.

(C) hao-0000620.description: (C): The hind wing third axillary muscle that originates from the metapleuron and inserts on the third axillary sclerite of the hind wing.
(C) hao-0000620.label_original: metapleuro-third axillary sclerite of hind wing muscle

(C) hao-0000623.description: (C): The area that is elevated and extends along the posterior margin of the metanotum from the metascutellum to the supraalar area.

(C) hao-0000624.description: (C): The carina that delimits laterally the metascutellum.

(C) hao-0000627.description: (C): The acetabulum that is concave, surrounds the nucha and accommodates the base of the metasoma.

(C) hao-0000628.description: (C): The eusternum that is located in the metathorax.

(C) hao-0000632.description: (C): The epimeron that is located on the metapleuron and is located posteriorly of the metapleural sulcus.

(C) hao-0000633.description: (C): The scrobe that is located anteroventrally on the mesopectus and accommodates the mesocoxa.

(C) hao-0000634.description: (C): The episternum that is located anteroventrally of the metapleural sulcus.

(C) hao-0000636.description: (C): The leg that is located on the mesothorax.

(C) hao-0000637.description: (C): The depression that is located posteromedially on the mesoscutum.

(C) hao-0000638.description: (C): The joint that is composed of two sclerites that are connected with one articulation.

(C) hao-0000640.description: (C): The sensillum that corresponds to a multiporous plate.

(C) hao-0000933.description: (C): A sense organ embedded in the integument and consisting of one or a cluster of sensory neurons and associated sensory structures, support cells and glial cells forming a single organized unit with a largely bona fide boundary.

(C) hao-0000641.description: (C): The portion of tissue that is composed of contractile fibers.

(C) hao-0000642.description: (C): The apodeme that corresponds to the site of insertions of the lateral metapleuro-metanotal muscles.
(C) hao-0000642.label_original: muscle bearing process of the metanotum

(C) hao-0000643.description: (C): The intrinsic leg muscle that originates within the tibia and femur and has a long tendon that inserts through the terminal tarsomere onto the unguitractor.

(C) hao-0001466.description: (C): The leg muscle that inserts and originates in the leg.

(C) hao-0001043.description: (C): The sclerite that corresponds to the site of insertion of the flexor of the pretarsus.

(C) hao-0000644.description: (C): The area that is located posteroventrally on the pronotum and corresponds to the site of origin of first flexor of the fore wing muscle.

(C) hao-0000645.description: (C): The ridge that extends along the anterior margin of the netrion.

(C) hao-0000646.description: (C): The sulcus that  anteriorly delimits the netrion.

(C) hao-0000647.description: (C): The line that extends submedially along the mesoscutum and corresponds to the median border of the site of origin of the first mesopleuro-mesonotal muscle.

(C) hao-0000649.description: (C): The suture that is located between the mesonotum and mesopleuron.

(C) hao-0000651.description: (C): The area that is raised and surrounds the propodeal foramen.

(C) hao-0000652.description: (C): The area that is located on the cranium and is delimited anteriorly by the occipital suture and posteriorly by the postoccipital sutures.

(C) hao-0000653.description: (C): The carina that surrounds dorsolaterally the occiput.

(C) hao-0000654.description: (C): The fossa that articulates with the cranial condyle of the propleuron.

(C) hao-0000655.description: (C): The depression that is located submedially on the occiput, ventral to the occipital carina.

(C) hao-0000658.description: (C): The area that is concave and surrounds the postocciput.

(C) hao-0000656.description: (C): The sulcus that is paired, extends dorsally from the posterior tentorial pit towards lateral ocellus and corresponds with the occipital ridge.

(C) hao-0000659.description: (C): The apodeme that corresponds to the site of origin of the occlusor muscle of the thoracic spiracle.

(C) hao-0000660.description: (C): The depression that extends along the lateral margin of a lateral ocellus or along anterior margin of the anterior ocellus.

(C) hao-0000662.description: (C): The anatomical line that is shortest and connects the compound eye and the lateral ocellus.

(C) hao-0000664.description: (C): The sulcus that extends along the margin of compound eye and corresponds to the circumocular ridge.

(C) hao-0000666.description: (C): One of the facets of the compound eye.

(C) hao-0000668.description: (C): The sclerite that functions like a lid and covers the spiracular opening.

(C) hao-0000671.description: (C): The sclerite that is located proximodorsally on the pretarsus and connects the distodorsal margin of the telotarsus with the dorsal part of the arolium.

(C) hao-0000673.description: (C): The band that extends along the medial margin of the eye.

(C) hao-0000675.description: (C): The carina that is longitudinal and extends anteriorly on the lateral surface of the mandible.

(C) hao-0000676.description: (C): The impression that extends dorsally of the condylar carina of the mandible.

(C) hao-0000677.description: (C): The line that extends along the border between the eye and gena.

(C) hao-0000678.description: (C): The anatomical space that receives sperm ejected from the aedeagus.

(C) hao-0000679.description: (C): The anatomical cluster that is composed of the first valvulae, second valvulae, third valvulae, first valvifers, second valvifers and female T9.

(C) hao-0001768.description: (C): The anatomical cluster that composed of the median oviduct, spermatheca and the ovipositor apparatus.

(C) hao-0000680.description: (C): The anatomical cluster that is composed of the third valvulae.

(C) hao-0000681.description: (C): The sensillum with a paddle-shaped cuticular componenet on the probasitarsus.

(C) hao-0000682.description: (C): The area that is located on the stipes and which articulates with the maxillary palp.

(C) hao-0000958.description: (C): The appendage that is connected posteroproximally to the hypostoma, anteroproximally and lateroproximally to the mandible and medioproximally to the labium and the hypopharynx via conjunctiva, is connected to the cranium via muscles and that bears the maxillary palp.

(C) hao-0000684.description: (C): The ridge that extends along the anterior margin of the metapectus.

(C) hao-0000685.description: (C): The sulcus that corresponds to the paracoxal ridge.

(C) hao-0000686.description: (C): The lobe that is connected to the distal margin of the prementum posteroproximally, to the premental hypopharynx proximolaterally and anteroproximally, to the glossa proximomedially and bears the basiparaglossal brush and the paraglossal sclerite.

(C) hao-0000687.description: (C): The labial muscle that arises from the ventral part of the prementum, anterior to the origin of the premento-glossal muscle and ventral premento-salivarial muscle and inserts just distally of the distal margin of the prementum.

(C) hao-0000688.description: (C): The projection that is located distolaterally on the hypostoma and extends to the clypeus separating the mandibular socket from the oral foramen.

(C) hao-0000689.description: (C): The area that is located on the face and delimited ventromedially by the epistomal sulcus.

(C) hao-0000690.description: (C): The carina that surrounds the compound eye.

(C) hao-0000691.description: (C): The area that is located ventromedially on the paraocular area and is surrounded partly by the epistomal sulcus.

(C) hao-0000692.description: (C): The area that is the dorsomedian part of the gonostipes and is the site of origin of the distodorsal and proximodorsal gonostyle/volsella complex-penisvalval muscles.

(C) hao-0000693.description: (C): The area that is narrow and connects the parapenis with the rest of the gonostipes.

(C) hao-0000694.description: (C): The signum that is located between the notaulus and the parascutal carina and corresponds to the site of origin of the dorsoventral indirect flight muscle.

(C) hao-0000695.description: (C): The area that is delimited medially by the parapsidal line and laterally by the parascutal carina.

(C) hao-0000696.description: (C): The area that is located on the upper face, is delimited medially by the antennal scrobe and laterally by the inner orbit.

(C) hao-0000697.description: (C): The rim that extends along the lateral margin of the lateral area of the mesoscutum and delimits the preaxilla.

(C) hao-0000698.description: (C): The projection that is lateral and located apically on the penisvalva.

(C) hao-0001047.description: (C): The area that is the distal part of the penisvalva dorsally of the ergot.

(C) hao-0000699.description: (C): The area that is lateral on the cranium between the frontal and occipital areas, separated above by the coronal suture.

(C) hao-0000700.description: (C): The band that is located on the anterior part of the larval head.

(C) hao-0000701.description: (C): The male genitalia muscle that arises from the proximal apex of the parossiculus and inserts on the medially on the penisvalva. The muscle inserts on the ergot if present.

(C) hao-0000702.description: (C): The male genitalia muscle that originates from the parossiculus and inserts on the endophallic membrane around the phallotrema.

(C) hao-0000704.description: (C): The area that is round and differs from surrounding regions in sculpture, setae, and/or pigmentation.

(C) hao-0000706.description: (C): The antennal segment that is connected proximally to the scape and distally to the flagellum.

(C) hao-0000708.description: (C): The male genitalia muscle that arises from the median surface of the proximal apex of the penisvalva and inserts on the endophallus.

(C) hao-0000709.description: (C): The gonossiculal muscle that arises from the penisvalva.

(C) hao-0000710.description: (C): The male genitalia muscle that arises from the medial surface of the proximal part of the penisvalva and inserts on the endophallus just around the phallotrema.

(C) hao-0000711.description: (C): The anatomical cluster that comprises the ventral marginal of the cranium, including the clypeus, the pleurostomata, and the hyperstomata.

(C) hao-0000712.description: (C): A sclerotic ring surrounding the outer spiracular opening.

(C) hao-0000714.description: (C): The anatomical space that is the distal opening of the endophallus.

(C) hao-0000715.description: (C): The developing adult after pupal-adult apolysis, i.e. from stage P8 (when yellow eye color first becomes visible through the pupal case), to eclosion.

(C) hao-0000717.description: (C): The anatomical cluster that is composed of fine, dense setae, acanthae or microtrichiae.

(C) hao-0000719.description: (C): The sclerite that is located proximoventrally on the pretarsus and is connected proximally with the unguitractor plate and distally with the arolium.

(C) hao-0000721.description: (C): The apophysis that is adjacent to the pleural ridge.

(C) hao-0000722.description: (C): The anatomical cluster composed of the pro-, meso-, and metapleura.

(C) hao-0000726.description: (C): The fossa that is located on the dorsal margin of the pleuron and accommodates the second axillary sclerite.

(C) hao-0000727.description: (C): The sclerite that is located on the pleuron.

(C) hao-0000728.description: (C): The line of separation between the pleural region and the venter, lying mesad of the limb bases, but obscured when the latter are fused with the sterna.

(C) hao-0000730.description: (C): The area that extends on the ventral (anterior) margin of the cranium along the site of origin of the conjunctiva connecting the mandible with the cranium and is delimited posteriorly (ventrally) by the posterior (ventral) margin of the pleurostomal fossa and anteriorly (dorsally) by the anterior (dorsal) margin of the pleurostomal condyle and laterally by the mouth margin.

(C) hao-0000731.description: (C): The condyle that is located on the anterior (dorsal) margin of the pleurostoma and inserts into the mandibular acetabulum.

(C) hao-0000732.description: (C): The fossa that is located postero- (ventro-) medially on the pleurostoma and accommodates the mandibular condyle.

(C) hao-0000733.description: (C): The ridge that extends between the pleurostomal fossa and pleurostomal condyle and delimits the lateral margin of the pleurostoma.

(C) hao-0000734.description: (C): The suture that is dorsal to the mandible and is part of the subgenal suture.

(C) hao-0000735.description: (C): The carina that arises from the anterior margin of the abdominal tergum 1 medially of the propodeal spiracle extends to the posterior propodeal projection.

(C) hao-0000736.description: (C): The wing fold that is located between the mediocubital field and axillary region.

(C) hao-0000737.description: (C): The wing fold that is located between the cubital field and the first vannal vein.

(C) hao-0000738.description: (C): The area that is delimited laterally by the metapleural carina and medially by the plica.

(C) hao-0001249.description: (C): The area of the metapectal-propodeal complex that is located posterior to the metapleural carina.

(C) hao-0000739.description: (C): The area corresponding to the upper margin of the mandible, above the acetabular groove, commonly ending in the preapical tooth or teeth.

(C) hao-0000740.description: (C): The setiferous patch that is located ventrally on the mesopleuron posterior to the epicnemial carina.

(C) hao-0000741.description: (C): The sulcus that extends posteriorly along the epicnemial carina.

(C) hao-0000742.description: (C): The process that is located anterolaterally on the mesoscutellar-axillar complex and separates the site of origin of the fore wing from the site of origin of the hind wing.

(C) hao-0000743.description: (C): The area that is located on the clypeus and is delimited by the epistomal sulcus and a medial transverse anatomical line.

(C) hao-0000744.description: (C): The usual sixth vein of the wing, associated basally with the cubitus.

(C) hao-0000745.description: (C): The mandibular muscle that arises posterodorsally from the cranium and inserts on the tendon attached anteroproximally on the mandible.

(C) hao-0000746.description: (C): The area that is located on the posteroventral corner of the preaxilla and articulates with the anterior extension of the lateral axillar area.

(C) hao-0000747.description: (C): The area that is delimited laterally distally and proximally by the sclerites that are connected to the distal margin of the prementum and receive the site of insertion of the premento-paraglossal muscle.

(C) hao-0000748.description: (C): The sclerite of the posterior glossal plate that is paired.

(C) hao-0000749.description: (C): The labral muscle that arises from the upper face laterally to the anterior fronto-labral muscle and inserts on the torma.

(C) hao-0001630.description: (C): The process that is located on the proximolateral corner of the labrum. The torma corresponds to the site of attachment for the posterior fronto-labral muscle.

(C) hao-0000751.description: (C): The area that extends along the posterior margin of the mesopleuron and is delimited anteriorly by the mesepimeral sulcus.

(C) hao-0000752.description: (C): The inflection that extends along the posterior margin of the mesepimeron, posteriorly of the subalar pit to the coxal articulation.

(C) hao-0000753.description: (C): The mesolaterophragmal muscle that originates from the mesofurca and inserts on the mesolaterophragma posterior to the site of origin of the anterior mesofuco-mesolaterophragmal muscle.

(C) hao-0000754.description: (C): The mesonoto-mesotrochanteral muscle that arises from the dorsal axillar area, posteriorly of the site of origin of the anterior mesonoto-mesotrochanteral muscle (if present) and inserts on the mesotrochanteral apodeme.

(C) hao-0001894.description: (C): The muscle that arises from the mesonotum and inserts on the mesotrochanter.

(C) hao-0000755.description: (C): The mesofurcal muscle that originates proximally from the mesofurca and inserts on the mesopleuron.

(C) hao-0000756.label_original: posterior mesopleuro-third axillary sclerite of fore wing muscle

(C) hao-0000757.description: (C): The line that extends along the posterior margin of the mesoscutellum and corresponds to the posterior mesoscutellar ridge.

(C) hao-0000758.description: (C): The articular process that is located on the lateral margin of the alinotum and articulates with the first axillary sclerite.

(C) hao-0000759.description: (C): The anatomical line that is the shortest between the margin of the lateral ocelli.

(C) hao-0000760.description: (C): The ridge that extends along the dorsal margin of the dorsal profurcal lamella and corresponds to the site of origin of the lateral profurco-procoxal muscle.

(C) hao-0000761.description: (C): The inflection that extends along the posterior margin of the pronotum and articulates with the anterior mesopleural inflection.

(C) hao-0000762.description: (C): The sulcus that extends parallel with the posterior margin of the pronotum and corresponds to the ridge of the posterior pronotal inflection.

(C) hao-0000763.description: (C): The propodeal spine that is located posteromedially of the first abdominal spiracle.

(C) hao-0001695.description: (C): The spine on the metapectal-propodeal complex that is paired and is medial to the propodeal spiracle.

(C) hao-0000764.description: (C): The line that extends just posterior of the posterior mesoscutellar ridge/mesoscutellar arms and delimits the posterior margin of the mesoscutellar pulsatory organ and the anterior margin of the mesopostscutellum.

(C) hao-0000765.description: (C): The area that is located posteriorly on the mesoscutum.

(C) hao-0000767.description: (C): The area that is limited medially by the transmetanotal carina and bears the postmedian metanotal wing process.

(C) hao-0000768.description: (C): The tentorial pit that corresponds to posterior tentorial arm.

(C) hao-0000769.description: (C): The spiracle that is located dorsally on the border between the mesopectus and the metapectus.

(C) hao-0000770.description: (C): The edge that is located at the intersection of the dorsal and lateral margins of the pronotum.

(C) hao-0000771.description: (C): The edge that is located at the intersection of the mesepimeral ridge and the inflected dorsal margin of the mesopleuron.

(C) hao-0000772.description: (C): The area that is limited anteriorly by the posterolateral pronotal sulcus.

(C) hao-0000773.description: (C): The carina that extends parallel to the posterolateral margin of the pronotum and delimits the posterolateral margin of pronotum.

(C) hao-0000774.description: (C): The sulcus that arises from the ventrolateral pit of the pronotum and reaches the posterolateral carina of the pronotum ventral to the anterior thoracic spiracle.

(C) hao-0000775.description: (C): The pit that corresponds to the dilator muscle apodeme.

(C) hao-0000776.description: (C): The area that is located on the occiput ventrally of the occipital foramen.

(C) hao-0000778.description: (C): The setiferous patch that is located on the postgena.

(C) hao-0000779.description: (C): The pit that corresponds to the ventral-most point of the posterior site of fusion of the ventral lamella of the tentorium.

(C) hao-0000780.description: (C): The sulcus that corresponds with the postgenal ridge.

(C) hao-0000781.description: (C): The groove that is median, vertical and extends between the occipital and oral foramina separating the postgenae.

(C) hao-0000783.description: (C): The abscissa that is marginal and located distal to the marginal vein.

(C) hao-0000784.description: (C): The fossa that is located on the lateral axillar area and articulates with the posterior end of the first axillary sclerite of the fore wing.

(C) hao-0000785.description: (C): The anatomical cluster that is composed of the sclerites that are on the postmental area.

(C) hao-0000787.description: (C): The ridge that corresponds to the postoccipital sulcus.

(C) hao-0000788.description: (C): The sulcus that is located on the postoccipital suture.

(C) hao-0000789.description: (C): The line that delimits the postocciput from the cranium.

(C) hao-0000791.description: (C): The sulcus that extends between the posterior margin of the lateral ocelli.

(C) hao-0000792.description: (C): The area posterior to the imaginary line intersecting the lateral ocelli and anterior to the occipital carina.

(C) hao-0000793.description: (C): The carina that extends posteriorly from the genal sulcus.

(C) hao-0000794.description: (C): The carina that delimits anterolaterally the mesocoxal depression.

(C) hao-0000795.description: (C): The phragma that is located posteriorly on a thoracic segment.

(C) hao-0000796.description: (C): The area corresponding to the postcostal lip of a definitive sternal plate that includes the intersegmental sclerotization following.

(C) hao-0000797.description: (C): The area that corresponds to the narrow postcostal lip of a postnotal thoracic plate.

(C) hao-0000798.description: (C): The tooth that is located distodorsally on the mandible.

(C) hao-0001019.description: (C): The projection that is located distally on the mandible.

(C) hao-0000799.description: (C): The notch that is located on the margin of the second valvifer immediately anterior to the basal articulation of the second valvulae.

(C) hao-0000928.description: (C): The area of the second valvifer-second valvula-third valvula complex that is distal to the basal articulation and to the processus musculares and is limited medially by the median body axis.

(C) hao-0000801.description: (C): The carina that extends across the preaxilla and separates the articulation area for the tegula.

(C) hao-0000803.description: (C): The labial muscle that is unpaired, arises from the postmentum and inserts on the proximal margin of the prementum.

(C) hao-0000805.description: (C): The carina that is transverse and extends posteriorly of the lateral ocelli and compound eye and delimits anteriorly the preoccipital lunula.

(C) hao-0000806.description: (C): The sulcus that arises medially from the anterior margin of the occipital carina and extends towards the anterior ocellus.

(C) hao-0000807.description: (C): The area that is concave, is located on the vertex and is limited anteriorly by the preoccipital carina and posteriorly by the occipital carina.

(C) hao-0000808.description: (C): The pit that is located on upper face adjacent the anterior margin of the median ocellus and corresponds internally to a conical apodeme and not the tentorium.

(C) hao-0000810.description: (C): The carina that is located on the face, parallels the inner orbit and is paired.

(C) hao-0000811.description: (C): The intersegmentalia that is located on the mesopectus-pronotum intersegmental membrane and corresponds to the site of origin of the anterior thoracic spiracle occlusor muscle.

(C) hao-0000813.description: (C): The ridge that seperates the prescutum from scutum.

(C) hao-0000814.description: (C): The sulcus that sets off the prescutum from the scutum and corresponds to the prescutal ridge.

(C) hao-0000815.description: (C): The area that is located on the alinotum and is limited by the antecostal suture and prescutal suture.

(C) hao-0000816.description: (C): The sulcus that delimits anteriorly the speculum and corresponds to the anterior margin of the speculum.

(C) hao-0000817.description: (C): The area that is located between the first metasomal spiracle and metapleural arm and delimited laterally by the metapleural carina.

(C) hao-0000818.description: (C): The area that is located on the basisternum and is delimited by the sternacostal sulcus.

(C) hao-0000819.description: (C): The patch that is enlarged, sclerotized, and located at the apex of one or more wing veins on the anterior margin of the wing.

(C) hao-0000821.description: (C): The anatomical space that is the transition from the ductus ejaculatorius to the endophallus and therefore the transition from the internal to the external male genitalia.

(C) hao-0000823.description: (C): The discrimen that is located in the prothorax and corresponds to the prodiscrimenal lamella.

(C) hao-0000873.description: (C): The sclerite that is connected posteriorly to the propleuron and bears the prodiscrimen and the profurca.

(C) hao-0000824.description: (C): The discrimenal lamella that is located in the prothorax.

(C) hao-0000826.description: (C): The sternal apophysis that is paired, arises from the furcasternum of the prothorax and continuous with the prodiscrimenal lamella.

(C) hao-0000827.description: (C): The furcal pit that is located in the prothorax.

(C) hao-0000828.description: (C): The laterocervical muscle that arises medially from the anterior surface of the dorsal profurcal lamella.

(C) hao-0001116.description: (C): The thoracic muscle that inserts on the laterocervicalia.

(C) hao-0000830.description: (C): The depression that is dorsomedian and is located on the pronotum.

(C) hao-0000832.description: (C): The area of the pronotum that is subhorizontal and located posteriorly of the pronotal neck.

(C) hao-0000833.description: (C): The setiferous patch that corresponds with the transverse sulcus of the pronotum.

(C) hao-0000834.description: (C): The evagination that extends along the anterior margin of the pronotum and overlaps the head-propectus articulation.

(C) hao-0000836.description: (C): The area that is located dorsally on the posterior margin of the pronotum and overlaps the anterior thoracic spiracle.

(C) hao-0000838.description: (C): The area of the pronotum that is median, raised and limited laterally by sharp edges.

(C) hao-0000839.description: (C): The projection that is part of the pronotum.

(C) hao-0000840.description: (C): The corner that is located anterolaterally on the horizontal part of the collar.

(C) hao-0000841.description: (C): The area that is located on the pronotum and that is vertical.

(C) hao-0000842.description: (C): The sulcus that extends along the dorsal margin of the pronotum and delimits the dorsal pronotal area.

(C) hao-0000843.description: (C): The verricule that is located on the anterosubmedial pronotum.

(C) hao-0001076.description: (C): The setiferous patch that is composed of closely gathered setae.

Formally: x precedes y iff (x) <= (y), where  is a function that maps a process to a start point, and  is a function that maps a process to an end point.
