(OP) bfo-0000067.description: (OP): [copied from inverse property 'occurs in'] b occurs_in c =def b is a process and c is a material entity or immaterial entity& there exists a spatiotemporal region r and b occupies_spatiotemporal_region r.& forall(t) if b exists_at t then c exists_at t & there exist spatial regions s and s where & b spatially_projects_onto s at t& c is occupies_spatial_region s at t& s is a proper_continuant_part_of s at t

(OP) bspo-0000104.description: (OP): Crosses at an angle that is 90 degrees, or close to 90 degrees. In any non-linear organism, the main axes are rarely perpendicular when taken through the organism as a whole.

(OP) bspo-0000106.description: (OP): On the opposite side from. For example, the left arm is contralateral to the right arm (and the right leg).

(OP) bspo-0000113.description: (OP): Direcly opposite to. i.e. on the opposite side through the axis.

(OP) bspo-0000107.description: (OP): Further away from the surface of the organism. Thus, the muscular layer is deep to the skin, but superficial to the intestines.

(OP) bspo-0000108.description: (OP): Near the outer surface of the organism. Thus, skin is superficial to the muscle layer.

(OP) bspo-0000110.description: (OP): Closer to the left side of the organism. Example: The dorsal fin is right of the left pectoral fin, but is left of the right eye. On the type level: X left of Y <=> every instance x of X is left of some instance y of Y, and there exists some organism o such that x part of o and y part of o.

(OP) bspo-0000111.description: (OP): Closer to the right side of the organism. Example: The dorsal fin is right of the left pectoral fin, but is left of the right eye. On the type level: X left of Y <=> every instance x of X is right of some instance y of Y, and there exists some organism o such that x part of o and y part of o.

(OP) bspo-0000120.description: (OP): X in left side of Y <=> if Y is subdivided into two left and right portions, X is part of the left portion.

(OP) bspo-0000126.description: (OP): X in lateral side of Y <=> if X is in left side of Y or X is in right side of Y. X is often, but not always a paired structure

(OP) bspo-0000121.description: (OP): X in right side of Y <=> if Y is subdivided into two left and right portions, X is part of the right portion.

(OP) bspo-0000122.description: (OP): X posterior side of Y <=> if Y is subdivided into two anterior and posterior portions, X is part of the posterior portion.

(OP) bspo-0000123.description: (OP): X anterior side of Y <=> if Y is subdivided into two anterior and posterior portions, X is part of the anterior portion.

(OP) bspo-0000124.description: (OP): x in proximal side of y <=> if y is subdivided into two proximal and distal portions, y is part of the proximal portion.

(OP) bspo-0000125.description: (OP): x in distal side of y <=> if y is subdivided into two proximal and distal portions, y is part of the distal portion.

(OP) bspo-0001102.description: (OP): x is parallel t y iff x and y are lines or planes which when extended indefinitely do not cross.

(OP) bspo-0001106.description: (OP): X proximalmost part of Y <=> X is in proximal side of Y and X is adjacent to the proximal boundary of Y

(OP) bspo-0001107.description: (OP): x immediately deep to y iff x deep_to y and x is contiguous with y.

(OP) bspo-0015014.description: (OP): x immediately superficial to y iff x superficial to y and x is contiguous with y.

(OP) bspo-0001108.description: (OP): X distalmost part of Y <=> X is in distal side of Y and X is adjacent to the distal boundary of Y

(OP) bspo-0005001.description: (OP): X intersects median plane of iff X crosses the midine plane of Y.

(OP) bspo-0015101.description: (OP): X dorsal side of Y <=> if Y is subdivided into two dorsal and ventral portions, X is part of the dorsal portion.

(OP) ro-0000057.description: (OP): a relation between a process and a continuant, in which the continuant is somehow involved in the process

(OP) iao-0000136.description: (OP): A (currently) primitive relation that relates an information artifact to an entity.

(OP) iao-0000219.description: (OP): A primitive, instance-level, relation obtaining between an information content entity and some portion of reality. Denotation is what happens when someone creates an information content entity E in order to specifically refer to something. The only relation between E and the thing is that E can be used to 'pick out' the thing. This relation connects those two together. Freedictionary.com sense 3: To signify directly; refer to specifically

(OP) obi-0000312.description: (OP): A relation between a planned process and a continuant participating in that process. The presence of the continuant at the end of the process is explicitly specified in the objective specification which the process realizes the concretization of.

(OP) ro-0000056.description: (OP): a relation between a continuant and a process, in which the continuant is somehow involved in the process

(OP) ro-0002314.description: (OP): q characteristic of part of w if and only if there exists some p such that q inheres in p and p part of w.

(OP) ro-0000079.description: (OP): a relation between a function and an independent continuant (the bearer), in which the function specifically depends on the bearer for its existence

(OP) ro-0000085.description: (OP): a relation between an independent continuant (the bearer) and a function, in which the function specifically depends on the bearer for its existence

(OP) ro-0000080.description: (OP): a relation between a quality and an independent continuant (the bearer), in which the quality specifically depends on the bearer for its existence

(OP) ro-0000081.description: (OP): a relation between a role and an independent continuant (the bearer), in which the role specifically depends on the bearer for its existence

(OP) ro-0000087.description: (OP): a relation between an independent continuant (the bearer) and a role, in which the role specifically depends on the bearer for its existence

(OP) ro-0000091.description: (OP): a relation between an independent continuant (the bearer) and a disposition, in which the disposition specifically depends on the bearer for its existence

(OP) ro-0002000.description: (OP): a relation between a 2D immaterial entity (the boundary) and a material entity, in which the boundary delimits the material entity

(OP) ro-0002323.description: (OP): A mereological relationship or a topological relationship

(OP) ro-0002002.description: (OP): a relation between a material entity and a 2D immaterial entity (the boundary), in which the boundary delimits the material entity

(OP) ro-0002134.description: (OP): Relation between a 'neuron projection bundle' and a region in which one or more of its component neuron projections either synapses to targets or receives synaptic input.  T innervates some R  Expands_to: T has_fasciculating_neuron_projection that synapse_in some R.

(OP) ro-0002380.description: (OP): x is a branching part of y if and only if x is part of y and x is connected directly or indirectly to the main stem of y

(OP) ro-0002007.description: (OP): X outer_layer_of Y iff:  . X :continuant that bearer_of some PATO:laminar  . X part_of Y  . exists Z :surface  . X has_boundary Z  . Z boundary_of Y    has_boundary: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002002  boundary_of: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002000

(OP) ro-0002013.description: (OP): A 'has regulatory component activity' B if A and B are GO molecular functions (GO_0003674), A has_component B and A is regulated by B.

(OP) ro-0002014.description: (OP): A relationship that holds between a GO molecular function and a component of that molecular function that negatively regulates the activity of the whole.  More formally, A 'has regulatory component activity' B iff :A and B are GO molecular functions (GO_0003674), A has_component B and A is negatively regulated by B.

(OP) ro-0002015.description: (OP): A relationship that holds between a GO molecular function and a component of that molecular function that positively regulates the activity of the whole.  More formally, A 'has regulatory component activity' B iff :A and B are GO molecular functions (GO_0003674), A has_component B and A is positively regulated by B.

(OP) ro-0002018.description: (OP): w 'has process component' p if p and w are processes,  w 'has part' p and w is such that it can be directly disassembled into into n parts p, p2, p3, ..., pn, where these parts are of similar type.

(OP) ro-0002180.description: (OP): w 'has component' p if w 'has part' p and w is such that it can be directly disassembled into into n parts p, p2, p3, ..., pn, where these parts are of similar type.

(OP) ro-0002021.description: (OP): A relationship between a process and a barrier, where the process occurs in a region spanning the barrier. For cellular processes the barrier is typically a membrane. Examples include transport across a membrane and membrane depolarization.

(OP) ro-0002479.description: (OP): p has part that occurs in c if and only if there exists some p1, such that p has_part p1, and p1 occurs in c.

(OP) ro-0002578.description: (OP): p directly regulates q iff p is immediately causally upstream of q and p regulates q.

(OP) ro-0002023.description: (OP): Process(P2) is directly negatively regulated by process(P1) iff: P1 negatively regulates P2 via direct physical interaction between an agent executing P1 (or some part of P1) and an agent executing P2 (or some part of P2).  For example, if protein A has protein binding activity(P1) that targets protein B and this binding  negatively regulates the kinase activity (P2) of protein B then P2 directly negatively regulated by P1.

(OP) ro-0002630.description: (OP): p directly negatively regulates q iff p is immediately causally upstream of q, and p negatively regulates q.

(OP) ro-0002024.description: (OP): Process(P2) is directly postively regulated by process(P1) iff: P1 positively regulates P2 via direct physical interaction between an agent executing P1 (or some part of P1) and an agent executing P2 (or some part of P2).  For example, if protein A has protein binding activity(P1) that targets protein B and this binding positively regulates the kinase activity (P2) of protein B then P2 is directly postively regulated by P1.

(OP) ro-0002629.description: (OP): p directly positively regulates q iff p is immediately causally upstream of q, and p positively regulates q.

(OP) ro-0002025.description: (OP): A 'has effector activity' B if A and B are GO molecular functions (GO_0003674),  A 'has component activity' B and B is the effector (output function) of B.  Each compound function has only one effector activity.

(OP) ro-0002224.description: (OP): x starts with y if and only if x has part y and the time point at which x starts is equivalent to the time point at which y starts. Formally: (y) = (x)  (y) < (x), where  is a function that maps a process to a start point, and  is a function that maps a process to an end point.

(OP) ro-0002230.description: (OP): x ends with y if and only if x has part y and the time point at which x ends is equivalent to the time point at which y ends. Formally: (y) > (x)  (y) = (x), where  is a function that maps a process to a start point, and  is a function that maps a process to an end point.

(OP) ro-0002100.description: (OP): Relation between a neuron and an anatomical structure that its soma is part of.

(OP) ro-0002104.description: (OP): Holds between a cell c and a protein complex or protein p if and only if that cell has as part a plasma_membrane[GO:0005886], and that plasma membrane has p as part.

(OP) ro-0002320.description: (OP): A relationship that holds via some environmental process

(OP) ro-0002170.description: (OP): a is connected to b if and only if a and b are discrete structure, and there exists some connecting structure c, such that c connects a and b

(OP) ro-0002176.description: (OP): c connects a if and only if there exist some b such that a and b are similar parts of the same system, and c connects b, specifically, c connects a with b. When one structure connects two others it unites some aspect of the function or role they play within the system.

(OP) ro-0002178.description: (OP): Relation between an arterial structure and another structure, where the arterial structure acts as a conduit channeling fluid, substance or energy.

(OP) ro-0002202.description: (OP): x develops from y if and only if either (a) x directly develops from y or (b) there exists some z such that x directly develops from z and z develops from y

(OP) ro-0002215.description: (OP): A relation between a material entity (such as a cell) and a process, in which the material entity has the ability to carry out the process.

(OP) ro-0002225.description: (OP): x develops from part of y if and only if there exists some z such that x develops from z and z is part of y

(OP) ro-0002254.description: (OP): x has developmental contribution from y iff x has some part z such that z develops from y

(OP) ro-0002256.description: (OP): t1 induced_by t2 if there is a process of developmental induction (GO:0031128) with t1 and t2 as interacting participants. t2 causes t1 to change its fate from a precursor anatomical structure type T to T', where T' develops_from T

(OP) ro-0002295.description: (OP): p results in the developmental progression of s iff p is a developmental process and s is an anatomical entity and p causes s to undergo a change in state at some point along its natural developmental cycle (this cycle starts with its formation, through the mature structure, and ends with its loss).

(OP) ro-0002387.description: (OP): x has the potential to develop into y iff x develops into y or if x is capable of developing into y

(OP) ro-0002488.description: (OP): x existence starts during y if and only if the time point at which x starts is after or equivalent to the time point at which y starts and before or equivalent to the time point at which y ends. Formally: x existence starts during y iff (x) >= (y) & (x) <= (y).

(OP) ro-0002492.description: (OP): Relation between continuant c and occurrent s, such that every instance of c ceases to exist during some s, if it does not die prematurely.

(OP) ro-0003000.description: (OP): a produces b if some process that occurs_in a has_output b, where a and b are material entities. Examples: hybridoma cell line produces monoclonal antibody reagent; chondroblast produces avascular GAG-rich matrix.

(OP) ro-0003001.description: (OP): a produced_by b iff some process that occurs_in b has_output a.

(OP) ro-0002163.description: (OP): A is spatially_disjoint_from B if and only if they have no parts in common

(OP) ro-0002177.description: (OP): a is attached to part of b if a is attached to b, or a is attached to some p, where p is part of b.

(OP) ro-0002567.description: (OP): A relation that holds between elements of a musculoskeletal system or its analogs.

(OP) ro-0002179.description: (OP): Relation between an collecting structure and another structure, where the collecting structure acts as a conduit channeling fluid, substance or energy away from the other structure.

(OP) ro-0002258.description: (OP): Candidate definition: x developmentally related to y if and only if there exists some developmental process (GO:0032502) p such that x and y both participates in p, and x is the output of p and y is the input of p

(OP) ro-0002388.description: (OP): x has potential to directly develop into y iff x directly develops into y or x is capable of directly developing into y
(OP) ro-0002388.label_original: has potential to directly develop into

(OP) ro-0002207.description: (OP): Candidate definition: x directly_develops from y if and only if there exists some developmental process (GO:0032502) p such that x and y both participate in p, and x is the output of p and y is the input of p, and a substantial portion of the matter of x comes from y, and the start of x is coincident with or after the end of y.

(OP) ro-0002211.description: (OP): p regulates q iff p is causally upstream of q, the execution of p is not constant and varies according to specific conditions, and p influences the rate or magnitude of execution of q due to an effect either on some enabler of q or some enabler of a part of q.

(OP) ro-0002411.description: (OP): p is causally upstream of q iff p is causally related to q, the end of p precedes the end of q, and p is not an occurrent part of q.

(OP) ro-0002212.description: (OP): p negatively regulates q iff p regulates q, and p decreases the rate or magnitude of execution of q.

(OP) ro-0002305.description: (OP): p is causally upstream of, negative effect q iff p is casually upstream of q, and the execution of p decreases the execution of q.

(OP) ro-0002213.description: (OP): p positively regulates q iff p regulates q, and p increases the rate or magnitude of execution of q.

(OP) ro-0002304.description: (OP): p is causally upstream of, positive effect q iff p is casually upstream of q, and the execution of p is required for the execution of q.

(OP) ro-0002216.description: (OP): c stands in this relationship to p if and only if there exists some p' such that c is capable_of p', and p' is part_of p.

(OP) ro-0002328.description: (OP): A grouping relationship for any relationship directly involving a function, or that holds because of a function of one of the related entities.

(OP) ro-0002500.description: (OP): A relationship between a material entity and a process where the material entity has some causal role that influences the process

(OP) ro-0002219.description: (OP): x surrounded_by y if and only if (1) x is adjacent to y and for every region r that is adjacent to x, r overlaps y (2) the shared boundary between x and y occupies the majority of the outermost boundary of x

(OP) ro-0002226.description: (OP): x develops_in y if x is located in y whilst x is developing

(OP) ro-0002231.description: (OP): x 'has starts location' y if and only if there exists some process z such that x 'starts with' z and z 'occurs in' y

(OP) ro-0002232.description: (OP): x 'has end location' y if and only if there exists some process z such that x 'ends with' z and z 'occurs in' y

(OP) ro-0002233.description: (OP): p has input c iff: p is a process, c is a material entity, c is a participant in p, c is present at the start of p, and the state of c is modified during p.

(OP) ro-0002234.description: (OP): p has output c iff c is a participant in p, c is present at the end of p, and c is not present in the same state at the beginning of p.

(OP) ro-0002255.description: (OP): inverse of has developmental contribution from

(OP) ro-0002385.description: (OP): x has potential to developmentrally contribute to y iff x developmentally contributes to y or x is capable of developmentally contributing to y
(OP) ro-0002385.label_original: has potential to developmentally contribute to

(OP) ro-0002386.description: (OP): x has potential to developmentally induce y iff x developmentally induces y or x is capable of developmentally inducing y

(OP) ro-0002324.description: (OP): A relationship that holds between entities participating in some developmental process (GO:0032502)

(OP) ro-0002263.description: (OP): c acts upstream of p if and only if c enables some f that is involved in p' and p' occurs chronologically before p, is not part of p, and affects the execution of p. c is a material entity and f, p, p' are processes.

(OP) ro-0002264.description: (OP): c acts upstream of or within p if c is enables f, and f is causally upstream of or within p. c is a material entity and p is an process.

(OP) ro-0002327.description: (OP): c enables p iff c is capable of p and c acts to execute p.

(OP) ro-0002418.description: (OP): p is 'causally upstream or within' q iff p is causally related to q, and the end of p precedes, or is coincident with, the end of q.

(OP) ro-0002285.description: (OP): x developmentally replaces y if and only if there is some developmental process that causes x to move or to cease to exist, and for the site that was occupied by x to become occupied by y, where y either comes into existence in this site or moves to this site from somewhere else

(OP) ro-0002384.description: (OP): x has developmental potential involving y iff x is capable of a developmental process with output y. y may be the successor of x, or may be a different structure in the vicinity (as for example in the case of developmental induction).

(OP) ro-0002296.description: (OP): p 'results in development of' c if and only if p is a developmental process and p results in the state of c changing from its initial state as a primordium or anlage through its mature state and to its final state.

(OP) ro-0040036.description: (OP): p has anatomical participant c iff p has participant c, and c is an anatomical entity
(OP) ro-0040036.label_original: results in changes to anatomical or cellular structure

(OP) ro-0002298.description: (OP): The relationship that links an entity with the process that results in the formation and shaping of that entity over time from an immature to a mature state.

(OP) ro-0002299.description: (OP): The relationship that links an entity with a process that results in the progression of the entity over time that is independent of changes in it's shape and results in an end point state of that entity.

(OP) ro-0004047.label_original: causally upstream of or within, positive effect

(OP) ro-0004046.label_original: causally upstream of or within, negative effect

(OP) ro-0002315.description: (OP): The relationship that links a specified entity with the process that results in an unspecified entity acquiring the features and characteristics of the specified entity
(OP) ro-0002315.label_original: results in acquisition of features of

(OP) ro-0002329.description: (OP): this relation holds between c and p when c is part of some c', and c' is capable of p.
(OP) ro-0002329.label_original: part of structure that is capable of

(OP) ro-0002331.description: (OP): c involved_in p if and only if c enables some process p', and p' is part of p

(OP) ro-0002431.description: (OP): c involved in or regulates p if and only if either (i) c is involved in p or (ii) c is involved in regulation of p
(OP) ro-0002431.label_original: involved in or involved in regulation of

(OP) ro-0002427.description: (OP): inverse of causally upstream of or within

(OP) ro-0002337.description: (OP): A relationship that holds via some process of localization

(OP) ro-0002338.description: (OP): This relationship holds between p and l when p is a transport or localization process in which the outcome is to move some cargo c from some initial location l to some destination.

(OP) ro-0002344.label_original: results in transport to from or in

(OP) ro-0002339.description: (OP): This relationship holds between p and l when p is a transport or localization process in which the outcome is to move some cargo c from a an initial location to some destination l.

(OP) ro-0002341.description: (OP): Holds between p and l when p is a transportation or localization process and the outcome of this process is to move c from one location to another, and the route taken by c follows a path that is aligned_with l

(OP) ro-0002342.description: (OP): Holds between p and m when p is a transportation or localization process and the outcome of this process is to move c from one location to another, and the route taken by c follows a path that crosses m.

(OP) ro-0002350.description: (OP): is member of is a mereological relation between a item and a collection.

(OP) ro-0002351.description: (OP): has member is a mereological relation between a collection and an item.

(OP) ro-0002372.description: (OP): m has_muscle_origin s iff m is attached_to s, and it is the case that when m contracts, s does not move. The site of the origin tends to be more proximal and have greater mass than what the other end attaches to.

(OP) ro-0002373.description: (OP): m has_muscle_insertion s iff m is attaches_to s, and it is the case that when m contracts, s moves. Insertions are usually connections of muscle via tendon to bone.

(OP) ro-0002375.description: (OP): A relationship that holds between two material entities in a system of connected structures, where the branching relationship holds based on properties of the connecting network.

(OP) ro-0002376.description: (OP): x tributary_of y if and only if x a channel for the flow of a substance into y, where y is larger than x. If x and y are hydrographic features, then y is the main stem of a river, or a lake or bay, but not the sea or ocean. If x and y are anatomical, then y is a vein.

(OP) ro-0002379.description: (OP): x spatially_coextensive_with y if and inly if x and y have the same location

(OP) ro-0002412.description: (OP): p is immediately causally upstream of q iff p is causally upstream of q, and the end of p is coincident with the beginning of q.

(OP) ro-0002407.description: (OP): p indirectly positively regulates q iff p is indirectly causally upstream of q and p positively regulates q.

(OP) ro-0012012.description: (OP): p indirectly regulates q iff p is indirectly causally upstream of q and p regulates q.

(OP) ro-0002409.description: (OP): p indirectly negatively regulates q iff p is indirectly causally upstream of q and p negatively regulates q.

(OP) ro-0002410.description: (OP): relation that links two events, processes, states, or objects such that one event, process, state, or object (a cause) contributes to the production of another event, process, state, or object (an effect) where the cause is partly or wholly responsible for the effect, and the effect is partly or wholly dependent on the cause.

(OP) ro-0002501.description: (OP): p is causally related to q if and only if p or any part of p and q or any part of q are linked by a chain of events where each event pair is one where the execution of p influences the execution of q. p may be upstream, downstream, part of, or a container of q.

(OP) ro-0002428.description: (OP): c involved in regulation of p if c is involved in some p' and p' regulates some p

(OP) ro-0002429.description: (OP): c involved in regulation of p if c is involved in some p' and p' positively regulates some p

(OP) ro-0002430.description: (OP): c involved in regulation of p if c is involved in some p' and p' negatively regulates some p

(OP) ro-0002432.description: (OP): c executes activity in d if and only if c enables p and p occurs_in d.  Assuming no action at a distance by gene products, if a gene product enables (is capable of) a process that occurs in some structure, it must have at least some part in that structure.

(OP) ro-0002433.description: (OP): p contributes to morphology of w if and only if a change in the morphology of p entails a change in the morphology of w. Examples: every skull contributes to morphology of the head which it is a part of. Counter-example: nuclei do not generally contribute to the morphology of the cell they are part of, as they are buffered by cytoplasm.

(OP) ro-0002434.description: (OP): A relationship that holds between two entities in which the processes executed by the two entities are causally connected.

(OP) ro-0002436.description: (OP): An interaction relationship in which the two partners are molecular entities that directly physically interact with each other for example via a stable binding interaction or a brief interaction during which one modifies the other.

(OP) ro-0002448.description: (OP): The entity A, immediately upstream of the entity B, has an activity that regulates an activity performed by B. For example, A and B may be gene products and binding of B by A regulates the kinase activity of B.    A and B can be physically interacting but not necessarily. Immediately upstream means there are no intermediate entity between A and B.

(OP) ro-0011002.description: (OP): The entity A has an activity that regulates an activity of the entity B. For example, A and B are gene products where the catalytic activity of A regulates the kinase activity of B.

(OP) ro-0002449.description: (OP): The entity A, immediately upstream of the entity B, has an activity that negatively regulates an activity performed by B.   For example, A and B may be gene products and binding of B by A negatively regulates the kinase activity of B.

(OP) ro-0002450.description: (OP): The entity A, immediately upstream of the entity B, has an activity that positively regulates an activity performed by B.   For example, A and B may be gene products and binding of B by A positively regulates the kinase activity of B.

(OP) ro-0002464.label_original: helper property (not for use in curation)

(OP) ro-0002473.description: (OP): x composed_primarily_of y if and only if more than half of the mass of x is made from y or units of the same type as y.

(OP) ro-0002487.label_original: relation between physical entity and a process or stage

(OP) ro-0002490.description: (OP): x existence overlaps y if and only if either (a) the start of x is part of y or (b) the end of x is part of y. Formally: x existence starts and ends during y iff ((x) >= (y) & (x) <= (y)) OR ((x) <= (y) & (x) >= (y))

(OP) ro-0002496.description: (OP): x existence starts during or after y if and only if the time point at which x starts is after or equivalent to the time point at which y starts. Formally: x existence starts during or after y iff  (x) >=  (y).

(OP) ro-0002489.description: (OP): x starts ends with y if and only if the time point at which x starts is equivalent to the time point at which y starts. Formally: x existence starts with y iff (x) = (y).

(OP) ro-0002491.description: (OP): x exists during y if and only if: 1) the time point at which x begins to exist is after or equal to the time point at which y begins and 2) the time point at which x ceases to exist is before or equal to the point at which y ends. Formally: x existence starts and ends during y iff (x) >= (y) & (x) <= (y) & (x) <= (y) & (x) >= (y)

(OP) ro-0002497.description: (OP): x existence ends during or before y if and only if the time point at which x ends is before or equivalent to the time point at which y ends.

(OP) ro-0002493.description: (OP): x existence ends with y if and only if the time point at which x ends is equivalent to the time point at which y ends. Formally: x existence ends with y iff (x) = (y).

(OP) ro-0002494.description: (OP): x transformation of y if x is the immediate transformation of y, or is linked to y through a chain of transformation relationships

(OP) ro-0002495.description: (OP): x immediate transformation of y iff x immediately succeeds y temporally at a time boundary t, and all of the matter present in x at t is present in y at t, and all the matter in y at t is present in x at t

(OP) ro-0002595.description: (OP): A relationship that holds between a material entity and a process in which causality is involved, with either the material entity or some part of the material entity exerting some influence over the process, or the process influencing some aspect of the material entity.
(OP) ro-0002595.label_original: causal relation between material entity and a process

(OP) ro-0002551.description: (OP): A relation between a segment or subdivision of an organism and the maximal subdivision of material entities that provides structural support for that segment or subdivision.

(OP) ro-0002566.description: (OP): The entity or characteristic A is causally upstream of the entity or characteristic B, A having an effect on B. An entity corresponds to any biological type of entity as long as a mass is measurable. A characteristic corresponds to a particular specificity of an entity (e.g., phenotype, shape, size).

(OP) ro-0002568.description: (OP): m1 has_muscle_antagonist m2 iff m1 has_muscle_insertion s, m2 has_muscle_insection s, m1 acts in opposition to m2, and m2 is responsible for returning the structure to its initial position.

(OP) ro-0002571.description: (OP): x lumen_of y iff x is the space or substance that is part of y and does not cross any of the inner membranes or boundaries of y that is maximal with respect to the volume of the convex hull.

(OP) ro-0002572.description: (OP): s is luminal space of x iff s is lumen_of x and s is an immaterial entity

(OP) ro-0002584.description: (OP): s 'has part structure that is capable of' p if and only if there exists some part x such that s 'has part' x and x 'capable of' p
(OP) ro-0002584.label_original: has part structure that is capable of

(OP) ro-0002586.description: (OP): p results in breakdown of c if and only if the execution of p leads to c no longer being present at the end of p

(OP) ro-0002592.description: (OP): p results in organization of c iff p results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of c

(OP) ro-0002596.description: (OP): Holds between c and p if and only if c is capable of some activity a, and a regulates p.

(OP) ro-0002597.description: (OP): Holds between c and p if and only if c is capable of some activity a, and a negatively regulates p.

(OP) ro-0002598.description: (OP): Holds between c and p if and only if c is capable of some activity a, and a positively regulates p.

(OP) ro-0004007.description: (OP): p 'has primary input ot output' c iff either (a) p 'has primary input' c or (b) p 'has primary output' c.

(OP) ro-0004008.description: (OP): p has primary output c if (a) p has output c and (b) the goal of process is to modify, produce, or transform c.

(OP) ro-0004009.description: (OP): p has primary input c if (a) p has input c and (b) the goal of process is to modify, consume, or transform c.

(OP) ro-0004031.description: (OP): Holds between an entity and an process P where the entity enables some larger compound process, and that larger process has-part P.

(OP) ro-0004032.label_original: acts upstream of or within, positive effect

(OP) ro-0004033.label_original: acts upstream of or within, negative effect

(OP) ro-0004034.description: (OP): c 'acts upstream of, positive effect' p if c is enables f, and f is causally upstream of p, and the direction of f is positive

(OP) ro-0004035.description: (OP): c 'acts upstream of, negative effect' p if c is enables f, and f is causally upstream of p, and the direction of f is negative

(OP) ro-0012003.description: (OP): p acts on population of c iff c' is a collection, has members of type c, and p has participant c

(OP) ro-0012011.description: (OP): p is indirectly causally upstream of q iff p is causally upstream of q and there exists some process r such that p is causally upstream of r and r is causally upstream of q.

(OP) ro-0015006.description: (OP): q1 different_in_magnitude_relative_to q2 if and only if magnitude(q1) NOT =~ magnitude(q2). Here, magnitude(q) is a function that maps a quality to a unit-invariant scale.

(OP) ro-0015007.description: (OP): q1 increased_in_magnitude_relative_to q2 if and only if magnitude(q1) > magnitude(q2). Here, magnitude(q) is a function that maps a quality to a unit-invariant scale.

(OP) ro-0015008.description: (OP): q1 decreased_in_magnitude_relative_to q2 if and only if magnitude(q1) < magnitude(q2). Here, magnitude(q) is a function that maps a quality to a unit-invariant scale.

(OP) ro-0015011.description: (OP): s3 has_cross_section s3 if and only if : there exists some 2d plane that intersects the bearer of s3, and the impression of s3 upon that plane has shape quality s2.

(OP) ro-0015012.description: (OP): q1 reciprocal_of q2 if and only if : q1 and q2 are relational qualities and a phenotype e q1 e2 mutually implies a phenotype e2 q2 e.

(OP) ro-0017001.description: (OP): X device utilizes material Y means X and Y are material entities, and X is capable of some process P that has input Y.

(OP) ro-0019000.description: (OP): A relationship that holds between a process and a characteristic in which process (P) regulates characteristic (C) iff:P results in the existence of C OR affects the intensity or magnitude of C.

(OP) ro-0019001.description: (OP): A relationship that holds between a process and a characteristic in which process (P) positively regulates characteristic (C) iff:P results in an increase in the intensity or magnitude of C.

(OP) ro-0019002.description: (OP): A relationship that holds between a process and a characteristic in which process (P) negatively regulates characteristic (C) iff:P results in a decrease in the intensity or magnitude of C.

(OP) pato2-different_in_magnitude_relati.description: (OP): OBSOLETE. q1 different_in_magnitude_relative_to q2 if and only if magnitude(q1) NOT =~ magnitude(q2). Here, magnitude(q) is a function that maps a quality to a unit-invariant scale.

(OP) pato2-similar_in_magnitude_relative.description: (OP): OBSOLETE. q1 similar_in_magnitude_relative_to q2 if and only if magnitude(q1) =~ magnitude(q2). Here, magnitude(q) is a function that maps a quality to a unit-invariant scale.

(AP) bfo-0000179.description: (AP): Relates an entity in the ontology to the name of the variable that is used to represent it in the code that generates the BFO OWL file from the lispy specification.

(AP) bfo-0000180.description: (AP): Relates an entity in the ontology to the term that is used to represent it in the the CLIF specification of BFO2

(AP) iao-0000111.description: (AP): The concise, meaningful, and human-friendly name for a class or property preferred by the ontology developers. (US-English)

(AP) iao-0000112.description: (AP): A phrase describing how a term should be used and/or a citation to a work which uses it. May also include other kinds of examples that facilitate immediate understanding, such as widely know prototypes or instances of a class, or cases where a relation is said to hold.

(AP) iao-0000116.description: (AP): An administrative note intended for its editor. It may not be included in the publication version of the ontology, so it should contain nothing necessary for end users to understand the ontology.

(AP) iao-0000117.description: (AP): Name of editor entering the term in the file. The term editor is a point of contact for information regarding the term. The term editor may be, but is not always, the author of the definition, which may have been worked upon by several people

(AP) iao-0000119.description: (AP): formal citation, e.g. identifier in external database to indicate / attribute source(s) for the definition. Free text indicate / attribute source(s) for the definition. EXAMPLE: Author Name, URI, MeSH Term C04, PUBMED ID, Wiki uri on 31.01.2007

(AP) iao-0000118.description: (AP): An alternative name for a class or property which means the same thing as the preferred name (semantically equivalent)

(AP) iao-0000233.description: (AP): An IRI or similar locator for a request or discussion of an ontology term.

(AP) iao-0000234.description: (AP): The name of the person, project, or organization that motivated inclusion of an ontology term by requesting its addition.

(AP) iao-0000412.description: (AP): For external terms/classes, the ontology from which the term was imported

(AP) iao-0000424.description: (AP): A macro expansion tag applied to an object property (or possibly a data property)  which can be used by a macro-expansion engine to generate more complex expressions from simpler ones

(AP) iao-0000589.description: (AP): An alternative name for a class or property which is unique across the OBO Foundry.

(AP) iao-0100001.description: (AP): Use on obsolete terms, relating the term to another term that can be used as a substitute

(AP) ro-0001900.description: (AP): An assertion that holds between an OWL Object Property and a temporal interpretation that elucidates how OWL Class Axioms that use this property are to be interpreted in a temporal context.

(AP) ro-0002161.description: (AP): x never in taxon T if and only if T is a class, and x does not instantiate the class expression 'in taxon some T'. Note that this is a shortcut relation, and should be used as a hasValue restriction in OWL.

(AP) ro-0002171.description: (AP): A is mutually_spatially_disjoint_with B if both A and B are classes, and there exists no p such that p is part_of some A and p is part_of some B.

(AP) ro-0002174.description: (AP): S dubious_for_taxon T if it is probably the case that no instances of S can be found in any instance of T.

(AP) ro-0002175.description: (AP): S present_in_taxon T if some instance of T has some S. This does not means that all instances of T have an S - it may only be certain life stages or sexes that have S

(AP) ro-0002475.description: (AP): A is has_no_connections_with B if there are no parts of A or B that have a connection with the other.

(AP) ro-0002575.description: (AP): relation p is the direct form of relation q iff p is a subPropertyOf q, p does not have the Transitive characteristic, q does have the Transitive characteristic, and for all x, y: x q y -> exists z1, z2, ..., zn such that x p z1 ... z2n y

(AP) ro-0002579.description: (AP): relation p is the indirect form of relation q iff p is a subPropertyOf q, and there exists some p' such that p' is the direct form of q, p' o p' -> p, and forall x,y : x q y -> either (1) x p y or (2) x p' y

(AP) ro-0002581.description: (AP): If R <- P o Q is a defining property chain axiom, then it also holds that R -> P o Q. Note that this cannot be expressed directly in OWL
(AP) ro-0002581.label_original: is a defining property chain axiom

(AP) ro-0002582.description: (AP): If R <- P o Q is a defining property chain axiom, then (1) R -> P o Q holds and (2) Q is either reflexive or locally reflexive. A corollary of this is that P SubPropertyOf R.
(AP) ro-0002582.label_original: is a defining property chain axiom where second argument is reflexive

(AP) ro-0002604.description: (AP): x is the opposite of y if there exists some distance metric M, and there exists no z such as M(x,z) <= M(x,y) or M(y,z) <= M(y,x).

(AP) ro-0004036.description: (AP): true if the two properties are disjoint, according to OWL semantics. This should only be used if using a logical axiom introduces a non-simple property violation.

(AP) ro-0040042.description: (AP): R is homemorphic for C iff (1) there exists some x,y such that x R y, and x and y instantiate C and (2) for all x, if x is an instance of C, and there exists some y some such that x R y, then it follows that y is an instance of C.

(AP) formats-hasNarrowSynonym.description: (AP): An alternative label for a class or property which has a more specific meaning than the preferred name/primary label.

(C) pato-0000414.description: (C): A branchiness quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking branches.

(C) pato-0000415.description: (C): A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being not curled or wound (especially in concentric rings or spirals).

(C) pato-0000460.description: (C): A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's deviation from normal or average.

(C) pato-0000462.description: (C): A quality denoting the lack of an entity.

(C) pato-0000610.description: (C): A morphological quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's affording unobstructed passage or view.

(C) pato-0000985.description: (C): A porosity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being incapable of admitting the passage of gas or liquid through pores or interstices.

(C) pato-0002364.description: (C): A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's length being notably lower than its width.

(C) pato-0001172.description: (C): An elasticity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's inability to recover its size and shape after deformation in any way.

(C) pato-0001691.description: (C): A contractility quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's inability of contracting or being contracted.

(C) pato-0002008.description: (C): A complete three dimensional shape in which there is a line connecting pair of points on the object that lies outside the object. Or: a shape with cavities. Contrast: concave.

(C) pato-0002040.description: (C): A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being convex on both sides or surface.

(C) pato-0000651.description: (C): A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being no longer merged with another entity.

(C) pato-0070006.description: (C): A cell morphology that inheres in neurons which have two principal dendrites that emerge from the soma and begin to branch some distance from it, have few spines, and branch in narrow fields. This is in contrast to bitufted morphology where branching occurs close to the soma.

(C) pato-0070026.description: (C): A cell morphology that inheres in neurons which possess three or more neurites, usually a single axon and many dendrites and dendritic branches.

(C) pato-0070010.description: (C): A cell morphology that inheres in neurons that have dendritic processes radiating from the cell body forming a star-like shape.

(C) pato-0002479.description: (C): A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being marked by narrow lines or grooves, usually parallel, that are oriented obliquely relative to the long axis of the bearer.

(C) pato-0070015.description: (C): A cell morphology that inheres in neurons which have a pyramidal shaped soma, a single axon, a large apical dendrite and multiple basal dendrites.

(C) pato-0070001.description: (C): A cell morphology that inheres in neurons which have a small round soma, a large number of short, smooth, or slightly beaded primary dendrites that give rise to only a few secondary branches, and a branched axon that establishes a dense axonal mesh with thin shafts.

(C) pato-0001501.description: (C): A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking complete growth, differentiation, or development.

(C) pato-0002011.description: (C): A structural quality which is held by a bearer when the latter's disposition the presence of abnormally proliferating masses of cells.

(C) pato-0002097.description: (C): A disposition inhering in a tumour by virtue of the bearer's disposition to progress, invade surrounding tissues or metastasize.

(C) pato-0070062.description: (C): A cell morphology that inheres in neurons with dendrites that stratify at two and only two locations.

(C) pato-0070063.description: (C): A cell morphology that inheres in neurons with dendrites that stratify at one and only one location.

(C) pato-0070046.description: (C): An affinity inhering in an anatomical structure by virtue of the bearer exhibiting a molecular interaction that stains and colors, pale-pink, with Wright-Giemsa stain.

(C) pato-0001871.description: (C): A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having the shape of a kidney.

(C) pato-0002506.description: (C): A surface feature shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's not having undulating edges forming lobes.

(C) pato-0070034.description: (C): A neuron projection quality that is a characteristic of neurons with both soma and projections entirely within the telencephalon.

(C) pato-0070028.description: (C): A neuron projection quality that is a characteristic of neurons whose soma is located in the telencephalon and that project to structures outside the telencephalon

(C) pato-0070030.description: (C): A neuron projection quality that is a characteristic of neurons with projections that terminate locally rather than distantly.

(C) pato-0070029.description: (C): A neuron projection quality that is a characteristic of neurons with soma in the cerebral cortex and projections to the thalamus.

(C) pato-0070016.description: (C): A pyramidal family morphology that inheres in neurons which have an apical tree which is oriented parallel to the pia.

(C) pato-0070012.description: (C): A cell morphology that inheres in neurons which have two clusters of primary dendrites that originate directly and extend from opposite ends of the soma, and axons that form a plexus which spreads widely. Compared to the narrow vertical axonal projection of bipolar morphology, and the 'horse-tail' axonal cluster of double boquet cells, bitufted morphology has wide horizontal axonal spans, and branching that occur close to the soma. Their vertical projection is also less extensive and crosses mostly to neighboring layers.

(C) pato-0070011.description: (C): A cell morphology that inheres in neurons which are small and round, and make highly specialized synapses with the axon initial segments of pyramidal neurons, wrapping them with candle-shaped synaptic 'cartridges'.

(C) pato-0070021.description: (C): A pyramidal cell morphology that inheres in neurons which have an apical tree which is oriented towards the white matter.

(C) pato-0070020.description: (C): A pyramidal cell morphology that inheres in neurons which lack a tuft formation but extend to small radial distances forming a star-like shape.

(C) pato-0070018.description: (C): A pyramidal cell morphology that inheres in neurons which have a distinct tuft formation, distal from the soma.

(C) pato-0070019.description: (C): A pyramidal cell morphology that inheres in neurons which lack a clear tuft formation but extend to large radial distances.

(C) pato-0070061.description: (C): A cell morphology that inheres in neurons with bitufted dendritic morphology but with the special feature of a tight fascicular axonal cylinder that resembles a 'horse tail'.

(C) pato-0001842.description: (C): A concentration quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's containing acid (hydrogen ions).

(C) pato-0001420.description: (C): A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to rise or float in a fluid medium such as water or air.

(C) pato-0000276.description: (C): A reproductive quality inhering in the young of an animal by virtue of their number.

(C) pato-0000004.description: (C): A quality of inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to move freely.

(C) pato-0000008.description: (C): A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's scalar absolute value of the rate of change of the bearer's position.

(C) pato-0001906.description: (C): A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's participation in movement.

(C) pato-0000011.description: (C): A time quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of how long the bearer has existed.

(C) pato-0000165.description: (C): A quality in which events occur in sequence.

(C) pato-0000014.description: (C): A composite chromatic quality composed of hue, saturation and intensity parts.

(C) pato-0000015.description: (C): A chromatic scalar-circular quality inhering in an object that manifests in an observer by virtue of the dominant wavelength of the visible light; may be subject to fiat divisions, typically into 7 or 8 spectra.

(C) pato-0001301.description: (C): An optical quality that is the mixture, purity or pattern of wavelengths of light perceived by the observer.

(C) pato-0000016.description: (C): A scalar optical property that is the intensity, value or amount of perceived light.

(C) pato-0000017.description: (C): A scalar chromatic property that is the degree of purity of perceived light.

(C) pato-0000018.description: (C): A luminous flux quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's emitting longer wavelength light following the absorption of shorter wavelength radiation; fluorescence is common with aromatic compounds with several rings joined together.

(C) pato-0001296.description: (C): A scalar optical quality which obtains by the magnitude of the light emitted by the bearer.

(C) pato-0000019.description: (C): A chromatic property that is the relative position of different hues or degrees of saturation.

(C) pato-0000060.description: (C): A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting repetition of placement of its parts.

(C) pato-0000021.description: (C): A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to harmonious coexistence.

(C) pato-0000186.description: (C): An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's behavior aggregate of the responses or reactions or movements in a given situation.

(C) pato-0000033.description: (C): A quality inhering in a substance by virtue of the amount of the bearer's there is mixed with another substance.

(C) pato-0002182.description: (C): A quality which inheres in a molecular entity, a single molecule, atom, ion, radical etc.

(C) pato-0000037.description: (C): A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's density, firmness, or viscosity.

(C) pato-0000039.description: (C): A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's orientation in space.

(C) pato-0000040.description: (C): A quality that is the extent of space between two entities.

(C) pato-0000043.description: (C): A quality of a physical entity inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer's molecules are being perceived by a taste and odorant receptors.

(C) pato-0000044.description: (C): A physical quality which inheres in a bearer by virtue of the number of the bearer's repetitive actions in a particular time.

(C) pato-0050000.description: (C): The number of repeated events per unit time, occurring in a repeating series. (e.g. the number of heart beats occurring over 1 minute)

(C) pato-0000047.description: (C): An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ability to undergo sexual reproduction in order to differentiate the individuals or types involved.

(C) pato-0000048.description: (C): A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's resistance to pressure, being broken, or pierced

(C) pato-0000049.description: (C): A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's possessing or displaying a distinctive feature in type or degree or effect or force.

(C) pato-0000050.description: (C): A time quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's expected maximum age.

(C) pato-0000056.description: (C): An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to synthesize a particular organic compound required for its growth.

(C) pato-0000057.description: (C): A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's occurrence.

(C) pato-0002323.description: (C): A temporal distribution pattern of process occurrences within a regulation/reference process.

(C) pato-0000058.description: (C): A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's molecules being are aerially dispersed and perceived by an odorant receptor.

(C) pato-0000059.description: (C): A parental quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of exhibiting the characteristic of a parent.

(C) pato-0000062.description: (C): A sleep quality defined by the mathematic properties of the relative time frames of the sleep cycle.

(C) pato-0001530.description: (C): A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's behavior.

(C) pato-0000066.description: (C): A texture quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having hair or bristles.

(C) pato-0000077.description: (C): A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the whether the bearer's disposition to react to a stimulus or an agent.

(C) pato-0000078.description: (C): A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's movement or variation characterized by the regular recurrence or alternation of different quantities or conditions.

(C) pato-0000080.description: (C): A physical quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the size of the bearer's maximum displacement from the 'normal' position, when periodic motion is taking place.

(C) pato-0001309.description: (C): A process quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's magnitude of the temporal extent between the starting and ending point.

(C) pato-0000082.description: (C): A rhythm quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the repetitiveness of bearer's rhythm.

(C) pato-0000083.description: (C): A quality that exists by virtue of being a particular point in the time of a cycle.

(C) pato-0000085.description: (C): A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to detect or perceive external stimulation.

(C) pato-0000119.description: (C): A 1-D extent quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's vertical dimension of extension.

(C) pato-0000122.description: (C): A 1-D extent quality which is equal to the distance between two points.

(C) pato-0000128.description: (C): A physical quality inhering in a bearer that has mass near a gravitational body. Important usage note: Note that this ontology has a class for a similar concept, mass (PATO:0000125). Mass and weight are not equivalent. For most use cases, the class mass is strongly preferred over weight.

(C) pato-0001035.description: (C): A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's rate of change of momentum.

(C) pato-0000133.description: (C): A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's placement which is defined by the angle between the bearer and an axis, or the angle between the bearer and another object.

(C) pato-0000140.description: (C): A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's spatial location relative to other objects in the vicinity.

(C) pato-0000146.description: (C): A physical quality of the thermal energy of a system.

(C) pato-0000152.description: (C): A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's sensitivity towards a fixed location or value where a change is observed; upper limit.

(C) pato-0000161.description: (C): A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's occurrence per unit time.

(C) pato-0000167.description: (C): A limited, often assigned period of activity.

(C) pato-0000169.description: (C): An organismal quality inhering in a bearer or a population by virtue of the bearer's disposition to survive and develop normally or the number of surviving individuals in a given population.

(C) pato-0000185.description: (C): A behavioral quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of having physical steadiness.

(C) pato-0000187.description: (C): A relational quality of occurrent inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ability to consume a resource.

(C) pato-0000188.description: (C): A behavioral quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having or lacking skillful and effective interaction of movement.

(C) pato-0000189.description: (C): A behavioral quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer's disposition to perceive differences between two or more stimuli.

(C) pato-0000273.description: (C): A reproductive quality inhering in an organism or population by virtue of the bearer's potential reproductive capacity ad measured by the number of gametes.

(C) pato-0001434.description: (C): An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ability to produce new life or offspring.

(C) pato-0000274.description: (C): A reproductive quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's initiating, sustaining, or supporting reproduction.

(C) pato-0001496.description: (C): A reproductive quality inhering in the young of an animal by virtue of the bearer's being cared for at one time.

(C) pato-0002317.description: (C): A convex quadrilateral is a parallelogram if and only if any one of the following statements are true:  1. Each diagonal divides the quadrilateral into two congruent triangles with the same orientation.  2. The opposite sides are congruent in pairs.  3. The diagonals bisect each other.  4. The opposite angles are congruent in pairs.  5. The sum of the squares of the sides equals the sum of the squares of the diagonals. (This is the parallelogram law)  6.It possesses rotational symmetry.  7.One pair of opposite sides are parallel and congruent.  8.Two pairs of adjacent angles are supplementary.

(C) pato-0001999.description: (C): The bearer of this quality has_part < n of the indicated entity type, where n is the normal amount for a comparable organism. Note that the bearer of the quality is the whole, not the part. Formally: If a bearer entity e has fewer parts of type X at time t, then the number of instances x of X at t such that x part_of e is < n, where n is either the normal number for comparable entities, or n is stated explicitly. This case includes the limit case, where the bearer lacks all parts of the specified type.
(C) pato-0001999.label_original: lacks parts or has fewer parts of type

(C) pato-0040031.description: (C): A width and length quality that is relatively large, where both width and length are increased.

(C) pato-0040032.description: (C): A distance traveled in a specific time that is relatively high.

(C) pato-0040033.description: (C): A distance traveled in a specific time that is relatively low.

(C) pato-0040034.description: (C): A broken quality where an entity is cracked or broken, usually a bone.

(C) pato-0040035.description: (C): A fractured quality where the fracture traverses the bone perpendicular to the axis of the bone.

(C) pato-0040036.description: (C): A fractured quality in which one of the fragments is driven into another fragment.

(C) pato-0040037.description: (C): A fractured quality where the fracture runs parallel to the long axis of a bone.

(C) pato-0040038.description: (C): A fractured quality where the fracture occurs at a plane oblique to the long axis of the bone.

(C) pato-0040039.description: (C): A fractured quality that occurs when torque (a rotating force) is applied along the axis of a bone.

(C) pato-0040040.description: (C): A fractured quality that is caused by a loss of bone mass (osteoporosis) that occurs as part of aging.

(C) pato-0040041.description: (C): A fractured quality in which the fragment of bone tears away from the main mass of bone as a result of physical trauma.

(C) pato-0040042.description: (C): A proportionality quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's decreased magnitude in respect to a related entity.

(C) pato-0040043.description: (C): A proportionality quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's increased magnitude in respect to a related entity.

(C) pato-0040044.description: (C): A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's components being torn, typically used for soft tissues or membranes.

(C) pato-0040045.description: (C): The rate or speed of the change in in number of a population.

(C) pato-0040046.description: (C): The rate or speed of the change in size of an individual entity.

(C) pato-0040047.description: (C): Existing or functioning as though broken into separate parts; disorganized; disunified.

(C) pato-0040048.description: (C): Red due to increase blood circulation in a defined area.

(C) pato-0040049.description: (C): A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population who are otherwise male of a non-hermaphroditic species who has ambiguous or atypical congenital development of the reproductive system.

(C) pato-0040050.description: (C): A phenotypic sex quality inhering in a  plant organism or a population of plants in which the flowers have two stamens.

(C) pato-0040051.description: (C): A phenotypic sex quality inhering in a  plant organism or a population of plants in which the flowers have only one stamen.

(C) pato-0040052.description: (C): A sequential hermaphroditic quality whereby organisms start out as female and change to male at a later life stage.

(C) pato-0070000.description: (C): A hermaphroditic quality that inheres in a population or organism where an organism changes is a different sexes during different life stages.

(C) pato-0040053.description: (C): A sequential hermaphroditic quality whereby organisms start out as male and change to female at a later life stage.

(C) pato-0040054.description: (C): A protogynous quality whereby organisms start out as female and change to hermaphrodite at a later life stage.

(C) pato-0040055.description: (C): A protandrous quality whereby organisms start out as male and change to hermaphrodite at a later life stage.

(C) pato-0040056.description: (C): A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population who are otherwise female of a non-hermaphroditic species who has ambiguous or atypical congenital development of the reproductive system.

(C) pato-0040058.description: (C): A quality denoting the lack of a physical entity or object, such as a chemical.

(C) pato-0040059.description: (C): A quality denoting the lack of a process or function.

(C) pato-0040072.description: (C): A quality inhering in a cell by virtue of the cell having a high nuclear/cytoplasmic ratio.

(C) pato-0045090.description: (C): The four cardinal directions or cardinal points are the directions north, east, south, and west, commonly denoted by their initials, N, E, S, W. East and west are at right angles to north and south, with east being in the clockwise direction of rotation from north and west being directly opposite east.

(C) pato-0045091.description: (C): North is one of the four compass points or cardinal directions. It is the opposite of south and is perpendicular to east and west.

(C) pato-0045093.description: (C): South is one of the four cardinal directions or compass points. South is the polar opposite of north and is perpendicular to east and west.

(C) pato-0045092.description: (C): East is one of the four cardinal directions or points of the compass. It is the opposite direction from west.

(C) pato-0045094.description: (C): West is one of the four cardinal directions or points of the compass. It is the opposite direction from east.

(C) pato-0050001.description: (C): The rate of output of a continuous process. Example include: growth rate, cell migration rate, enzyme reaction rate.

(C) pato-0055001.description: (C): A spatial distribution of a process in which the process occupies a smaller length, area, or volume than the reference process. For example, heterochromatin may form over a shorter length of a chromosome in a mutant than in wild type.
(C) pato-0055001.label_original: decreased spatial extent of a process

(C) pato-0055002.description: (C): A spatial distribution of a process in which the process occupies a greater length, area, or volume than the reference process. For example, heterochromatin may form over a shorter length of a chromosome in a mutant than in wild type.
(C) pato-0055002.label_original: increased spatial extent of a process

(C) pato-0055005.description: (C): A rate of output of a continuous process that is relatively high.

(C) pato-0055006.description: (C): A rate of output of a continuous process that is relatively low.

(C) pato-0060001.description: (C): A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being present in one sex and absent from the other in members of the same species.

(C) pato-0060002.description: (C): A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being present in males and absent from females in members of the same species.

(C) pato-0060003.description: (C): A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being present in females and absent from males in members of the same species.

(C) pato-0065001.description: (C): The breakdown, disintegration, destruction of an entity due to the breaking of cell membranes by any means.

(C) pato-0065002.description: (C): A degree of pigmentation quality that is diversified with patches, or irregularity.

(C) pato-0070002.description: (C): A cell morphology that inheres in multipolar neurons with densely branched terminal axonal arborizations that form basket-like structures surrounding and synapsing to the somas of target cells.

(C) pato-0070003.description: (C): A basket cell morphology that inheres in neurons with axonal arbors composed of frequent, short, curvy axonal branches that tend to be near their somata and within the same layer.

(C) pato-0070004.description: (C): A basket cell morphology that inheres in neurons that are large, and typically ascend to give rise to many long horizontally and vertically projecting axon collaterals that traverse neighboring columns and can extend through all cortical layers.

(C) pato-0070005.description: (C): A basket cell morphology that inheres in neurons which have simpler dendritic arbors (compared to small or large basket cell morphology), and an axonal plexus of intermediate density, composed of a few long, smooth axonal branches.

(C) pato-0070027.description: (C): A cell morphology that inheres in neurons with dendrites that are bidirectional, emerging from opposite ends of the soma, with the two arbors extending in radial or tangential directions.

(C) pato-0070007.description: (C): A cell morphology that inheres in neurons which are large and non-spiny, with dendrites radiating in a multipolar or bitufted pattern, often favouring the descending side, and axons that ascend directly from the superficial side of the soma, and travel upward without branching.

(C) pato-0070008.description: (C): A Martinotti cell morphology that inheres in neurons which have axons that form a horizontal ramification, making it T-shaped.

(C) pato-0070009.description: (C): A Martinotti cell morphology that inheres in neurons which have axons that form a fan-like plexus.

(C) pato-0070013.description: (C): A cell morphology that inheres in neurons which have spiny basal dendrites and resemble pyramidal cells but lose their apical dendrites as they mature. Their axons nearly always emerge from the descending side of the soma, but often recurve and ascend with arc-like collaterals.

(C) pato-0070017.description: (C): A pyramidal family morphology that inheres in neurons which have a standard pyramidal shape with its apical dendrite aligned vertically.

(C) pato-0070025.description: (C): A cell morphology that inheres in neurons with only one process, a neurite, that extends from the cell body. The neurite then branches to form dendritic and axonal processes.

(C) pato-0070033.description: (C): A physical quality inhering in a neuron by virtue of the relative location of its soma and the regions to which it projects and makes synaptic contacts in.

(C) pato-0070031.description: (C): A neuron projection quality that is a characteristic of neurons that project to the medulla oblongata from other brain regions.

(C) pato-0070036.description: (C): A quality inhering in a neuron's dendrites by virtue of the bearer's physical composition.

(C) pato-0070038.description: (C): A dendrite quality inhering in a neuron by virtue of the bearer's dendrite having spines.

(C) pato-0070039.description: (C): A dendrite quality inhering in a neuron by virtue of the bearer's dendrite having a terminal tuft.

(C) pato-0070040.description: (C): A dendrite quality inhering in a neuron by virtue of the bearer's dendrite having few or no recognizable dendritic spines.

(C) pato-0070041.description: (C): A dendrite quality inhering in a neuron by virtue of the bearer's dendrite having numerous swellings or varicosities along their length.

(C) pato-0070042.description: (C): A cell morphology that inheres in retinal neurons which have two principal fibres, an axon and a dendrite, that emerge from opposite end the soma.

(C) pato-0070059.description: (C): A texture quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being covered by iron oxide as a result of oxidation.

(C) pato-0070064.description: (C): A 3-D extent quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the spatial region that is defined by the maximal span of the bearer's dendritic arbor.

(C) pato-0080001.description: (C): A physical quality inhering in an entity exhibiting the physical charachteristics of a material that flows under applied force.

(C) pato-0085001.description: (C): An osmolarity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the total amount of ionic salts dissolved in the bearer.

(C) pato-0095001.description: (C): Quotient (or ratio) of surface area of an organism divided by the mass of the same organism

(C) pato-0095002.description: (C): An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's morphological and physiological adaptation for running.

(C) pato-0095003.description: (C): An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's morphological and physiological adaptation for digging and living underground.

(C) pato-0095004.description: (C): An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's morphological and physiological adaptation for living in trees.

(C) pato-0095005.description: (C): A quality of a process that happens during dawn and dusk.

(C) pato-0095006.description: (C): A quality of a process that happens during the hours of darkness.

(C) pato-0095007.description: (C): A quality of a process that happens during the hours of daylight.

(C) pato-0095008.description: (C): An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's morphological and physiological adaptation for participating in long-distance movement of conspecifics, usually on a seasonal basis.

(C) pato-0095009.description: (C): An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ability to burrow more than 20 cm deep into the soil and make permanent, vertical burrows.

(OP) ro-0002130.description: (OP): A general relation between a neuron and some structure in which it either chemically synapses to some target or in which it receives (chemical) synaptic input.

(OP) ro-0002102.description: (OP): Relation between a neuron and some structure its axon forms (chemical) synapses in.

(OP) ro-0002113.description: (OP): Relation between a neuron and some structure (e.g.- a brain region) in which it receives (chemical) synaptic input.

(OP) ro-0002110.description: (OP): Relation between a neuron and some structure (e.g.- a brain region) in which it receives (chemical) synaptic input.

(OP) ro-0002321.description: (OP): A relationship that is mediated in some way by the environment or environmental feature (ENVO:00002297)

(OP) ro-0002332.description: (OP): p regulates levels of c if p regulates some amount (PATO:0000070) of c

(OP) ro-0002503.description: (OP): q towards e2 if and only if q is a relational quality such that q inheres-in some e, and e != e2 and q is dependent on e2

(OP) ro-0002565.description: (OP): Holds between p and c when p is locomotion process and the outcome of this process is the change of location of c

(OP) ro-0002610.description: (OP): A relationship that holds between two entities, where the entities exhibit a statistical dependence relationship. The entities may be statistical variables, or they may be other kinds of entities such as diseases, chemical entities or processes.

(OP) ro-0015009.description: (OP): q1 similar_in_magnitude_relative_to q2 if and only if magnitude(q1) =~ magnitude(q2). Here, magnitude(q) is a function that maps a quality to a unit-invariant scale.

(OP) ro-0015015.description: (OP): A relation between a cell and molecule or complex such that every instance of the cell has a high number of instances of that molecule expressed on the cell surface.

(OP) ro-0015016.description: (OP): A relation between a cell and molecule or complex such that every instance of the cell has a low number of instances of that molecule expressed on the cell surface.

(OP) pato2-directly_associated_with.description: (OP): OBSOLETE. q1 directly_associated_with q2 iff q1 is dependent on q2, and the magnitude of q1 increases if the magnitude of q2 is increased, or the magnitude of q1 decreases if the magnitude of q2 is decreased. The relationship is not necessarily linear.

(OP) pato2-has_cross_section.description: (OP): OBSOLETE. s3 has_cross_section s3 if and only if : there exists some 2d plane that intersects the bearer of s3, and the impression of s3 upon that plane has shape quality s2.

(OP) pato2-inversely_associated_with.description: (OP): OBSOLETE. q1 inversely_associated_with q2 iff q1 is dependent on q2, and the magnitude of q1 decreases if the magnitude of q2 is increased, or the magnitude of q1 increases if the magnitude of q2 is decreased. The relationship is not necessarily linear.

(OP) pato2-reciprocal_of.description: (OP): OBSOLETE. q1 reciprocal_of q2 if and only if : q1 and q2 are relational qualities and a phenotype e q1 e2 mutually implies a phenotype e2 q2 e.

(AP) iao-0000231.description: (AP): Relates an annotation property to an obsolescence reason. The values of obsolescence reasons come from a list of predefined terms, instances of the class obsolescence reason specification.

(C) bspo-0000059.description: (C): Anatomical side that is centrally located on an organism or structure.

(C) bspo-0000012.description: (C): An axis that extends from an internal position to a more external position in the body or body part.

(C) bspo-0000008.description: (C): Sagittal plane that divides a bilateral body into unequal left and right parts.

(C) bspo-0000009.description: (C): Sagittal plane that divides bilateral body into equal left and right parts.

(C) bspo-0000014.description: (C): An axis that extends through an organism or organism part from the part of the organism or organism part attached to a substrate (basal) to the furthest from the attachment (apical). Note that the apical-basal axis is often used for organismal parts where there is attachment via a basal lamina or other structure.

(C) bspo-0000020.description: (C): Anatomical gradient that is distributed along the upper-lower axis.

(C) bspo-0000051.description: (C): Material anatomical entity defined by change in the value of some quantity per unit of distance across some spatial axis.

(C) bspo-0000021.description: (C): Anatomical gradient that is distributed along the deep-superficial axis.

(C) bspo-0000022.description: (C): The side that is higher relative to the substrate.

(C) bspo-0000023.description: (C): Anatomical gradient that is distributed along the apical-basal axis.

(C) bspo-0000024.description: (C): Anatomical gradient that is distributed along the proximal-distal axis.

(C) bspo-0000025.description: (C): The side that is lower relative to the substrate.

(C) bspo-0000033.description: (C): Anatomical region located deep within an organism or structure.

(C) bspo-0000034.description: (C): Anatomical region superficially located on the body or body part.

(C) bspo-0000052.description: (C): Anatomical gradient that is distributed along the anterior-posterior axis.

(C) bspo-0000053.description: (C): Anatomical gradient that is distributed along the dorsal-ventral axis.

(C) bspo-0000057.description: (C): Anatomical side that is located on the apical end of an organism or structure.

(C) bspo-0000058.description: (C): Anatomical side that is located on the basal end of an organism or structure.

(C) bspo-0000074.description: (C): Anatomical region located basally on the body or body part.

(C) bspo-0000075.description: (C): Anatomical region centrally located on the body or body part.

(C) bspo-0000127.description: (C): Anatomical region peripherally located on the body or body part.

(C) bspo-0000195.description: (C): An anatomical axis that extends from the side of the anatomical entity that is closer to an axis (adaxial) to the side that is further from the same axis (abaxial).

(C) bspo-0000196.description: (C): An anatomical axis that extends from the center of the body outwards or externally.
