(C) bspo-0000197.description: (C): An anatomical axis that is perpendicular to an apical/basal axis or proximal/distal axis and extends from the center of an axis (shoot axis or root in the case of plants) to any point on the exterior of the axis.

(C) bspo-0000198.description: (C): An axis that extends from the oral opening to the furthest point in an organism that is directly opposite.

(C) bspo-0000199.description: (C): An axis that extends from the animal end of an egg or early embryo to the opposite, vegetal end. In animals with yolk-bearing eggs, the vegetal end is the yolk bearing pole. (pertains to animals only - both vertebrate and invertebrate embryos).

(C) bspo-0000200.description: (C): An axis of a plant structure that is determined by the direction of apical growth, either by an apical meristem or an apical cell. Apical is toward the direction of apical growth: toward the tip of a growing shoot axis, root, thallus, or non-vascular leaf. Basal is away from the direction of apical growth: toward the root-shoot junction in the case of the primary root or stem, toward the primary root or stem for higher order roots or branches, toward the point of attachment for non-vascular leaves, and toward the original point of growth (as determined in the embryo) for thalli.
(C) bspo-0000200.label_original: apical-basal axis relative to direction of growth

(C) bspo-0000201.description: (C): Anatomical plane that is perpendicular to a radial plane.

(C) bspo-0000202.description: (C): Anatomical plane that follows the two dimensions specified by an apical-basal axis relative to direction of growth and a medial-lateral axis.

(C) bspo-0000373.description: (C): Anatomical surface that is located on the apical side of the body or body part.

(C) bspo-0000374.description: (C): Anatomical surface that is located on the basal side of the body or body part.

(C) bspo-0000381.description: (C): Anatomical surface that is located on the same side of an organism or structure.

(C) bspo-0000673.description: (C): Anatomical margin that is located on the apical side of the body or body part.

(C) bspo-0000674.description: (C): Anatomical margin that is located on the basal side of the body or body part.

(C) bspo-0001001.description: (C): An axis that extends from the center of organism to one or other side.

(OP) bspo-0000105.description: (OP): On the same side as. For example, the left arm is ipsilateral to the left leg.

(OP) bspo-0000114.description: (OP): X lateral to y if x is further from the midsagittal plane than y.

(OP) bspo-0000115.label_original: X medial to y if x is closer to the midsagittal plane than y.

(OP) bspo-0020001.description: (OP): X in_central_side Y <=> if Y is subdivided into left and right portions around some median divisor, all parts of X are closer to the median divisor than the outermost lateral sides.

(OP) bspo-0001100.description: (OP): X superficial part of Y <=> if Y is subdivided into two superficial and deep portions, X is part of the superficial portion.

(OP) bspo-0001101.description: (OP): X superficial part of Y <=> if Y is subdivided into two superficial and deep portions, X is part of the deep portion.

(OP) bspo-0001114.description: (OP): x preaxial to y iff x is further along the preaxial-postaxial axis than y, towards the postaxial side.

(OP) bspo-0015004.description: (OP): A relation between an axis and a part of an organism, in which the part defines the initial point of the axis.

(OP) bspo-0015009.description: (OP): x immediately anterior to y iff x anterior to y and x is contiguous with y.

(OP) bspo-0015012.description: (OP): x immediately posterior to y iff x posterior_to y and x is contiguous with y.

(OP) bspo-0015010.description: (OP): x immediately distal to y iff x distal to y and x is contiguous with y.

(OP) bspo-0015013.description: (OP): x immediately proximal to y iff x proximal to y and x is contiguous with y.

(OP) bspo-0015011.description: (OP): x immediately dorsal to y iff x dorsal to y and x is contiguous with y.

(OP) bspo-0015015.description: (OP): x immediately ventral to y iff x ventral to y and x is contiguous with y.

(OP) bspo-0015016.description: (OP): x immediately left of y iff x left_of y and x is contiguous with y.

(OP) bspo-0015017.description: (OP): x immediately right of y iff x right of y and x is contiguous with y.

(OP) bspo-0015102.description: (OP): X ventral side of Y <=> if Y is subdivided into two dorsal and ventral portions, X is part of the ventral portion.

(OP) bspo-0015201.description: (OP): nearer to the oral opening of the organism, on the oral-aboral axis.

(OP) bspo-0015202.description: (OP): nearer to the aboral opening of the organism, on the oral-aboral axis.

(OP) bspo-0020002.description: (OP): A relation between an axis and a part of an organism, in which the part defines the initial point of the axis.

(OP) bspo-0030003.description: (OP): x dorsalmost_part_of y iff x part_of y and there is no z which is part_of y and is more dorsal than x but not part_of x; x is adjacent to the dorsal boundary of y

(OP) bspo-0030004.description: (OP): x anteriormost_part_of y iff x part_of y and there is no z which is part_of y and is more anterior than x but not part_of x; x is adjacent to the anterior boundary of y

(OP) bspo-0030005.description: (OP): x lateralmost_part_of y iff x part_of y and there is no z which is part_of y and is more lateral than x but not part_of x; x is adjacent to the lateral boundary of y

(OP) bspo-0030006.description: (OP): X medial side of Y <=> if Y is subdivided into two medial and lateral portions, X is part of the medial portion.

(OP) bspo-0030007.description: (OP): x medialmost_part_of y iff x part_of y and there is no z which is part_of y and is more medial than x but not part_of x; x is adjacent to the medial boundary of y

(OP) bspo-1000000.description: (OP): x preaxial to y iff x is further along the preaxial-postaxial axis than y, towards the front.

(C) iao-8000001.description: (C): An ontology module that comprises only of asserted axioms local to the ontology, excludes import directives, and excludes axioms or declarations from external ontologies.

(C) iao-8000002.description: (C): An ontology module that is intended to be directly edited, typically managed in source control, and typically not intended for direct consumption by end-users.

(C) iao-8000003.description: (C): An ontology module that is intended to be the primary release product and the one consumed by the majority of tools.

(C) iao-8000004.description: (C): An ontology module that consists entirely of axioms that connect or bridge two distinct ontology modules. For example, the Uberon-to-ZFA bridge module.

(C) iao-8000005.description: (C): A subset ontology module that is intended to be imported from another ontology.

(C) iao-8000006.description: (C): An ontology module that is extracted from a main ontology module and includes only a subset of entities or axioms.

(C) iao-8000007.description: (C): A subset ontology that is intended as a whitelist for curators using the ontology. Such a subset will exclude classes that curators should not use for curation.

(C) iao-8000008.description: (C): An ontology module that is intended for usage in analysis or discovery applications.

(C) iao-8000009.description: (C): A subset ontology that is largely comprised of a single layer or strata in an ontology class hierarchy. The purpose is typically for rolling up for visualization. The classes in the layer need not be disjoint.

(C) iao-8000010.description: (C): A subset of an ontology that is intended to be excluded for some purpose. For example, a blacklist of classes.

(C) iao-8000011.description: (C): An imported ontology module that is derived from an external ontology. Derivation methods include the OWLAPI SLME approach.

(C) iao-8000012.description: (C): A subset ontology that is crafted to either include or exclude a taxonomic grouping of species.

(C) iao-8000013.description: (C): An ontology module that contains axioms generated by a reasoner. The generated axioms are typically direct SubClassOf axioms, but other possibilities are available.

(C) iao-8000014.description: (C): An ontology module that is automatically generated, for example via a SPARQL query or via template and a CSV.

(C) iao-8000015.description: (C): An ontology module that is automatically generated from a template specification and fillers for slots in that template.

(C) iao-8000018.description: (C): A subset ontology that is designed for basic applications to continue to make certain simplifying assumptions; many of these simplifying assumptions were based on the initial version of the Gene Ontology, and have become enshrined in many popular and useful tools such as term enrichment tools.    Examples of such assumptions include: traversing the ontology graph ignoring relationship types using a naive algorithm will not lead to cycles (i.e. the ontology is a DAG); every referenced term is declared in the ontology (i.e. there are no dangling clauses).    An ontology is OBO Basic if and only if it has the following characteristics:  DAG  Unidirectional  No Dangling Clauses  Fully Asserted  Fully Labeled  No equivalence axioms  Singly labeled edges  No qualifier lists  No disjointness axioms  No owl-axioms header  No imports

(C) iao-8000019.label_original: ontology module subsetted by OWL profile

(C) iao-0000003.description: (C): A measurement unit label is as a label that is part of a scalar measurement datum and denotes a unit of measure.

(C) iao-0000109.description: (C): A measurement datum is an information content entity that is a recording of the output of a measurement such as produced by a device.

(C) iao-0000400.description: (C): A cartesian spatial coordinate datum is a representation of a point in a spatial region, in which equal changes in the magnitude of a coordinate value denote length qualities with the same magnitude

(C) iao-0000416.description: (C): A scalar measurement datum that is the result of measuring a temporal interval

(C) iao-0000032.description: (C): A scalar measurement datum is a measurement datum that is composed of two parts, numerals and a unit label.

(C) iao-0000010.description: (C): Software is a plan specification composed of a series of instructions that can be   interpreted by or directly executed by a processing unit.

(C) iao-0000096.description: (C): A source code module is a directive information entity that specifies, using a programming language, some algorithm.

(C) iao-0000310.description: (C): A collection of information content entities intended to be understood together as a whole

(C) iao-0000100.description: (C): A data item that is an aggregate of other data items of the same type that have something in common. Averages and distributions can be determined for data sets.

(C) bfo-0000005.description: (C): A continuant  that is either dependent on one or other independent continuant  bearers or inheres in or is borne by other entities.

(C) bfo-0000140.description: (C): b is a continuant fiat boundary = Def. b is an immaterial entity that is of zero, one or two dimensions and does not include a spatial region as part. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [029-001])

(C) bfo-0000035.description: (C): p is a process boundary =Def. p is a temporal part of a process & p has no proper temporal parts. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [084-001])

(C) bfo-0000144.description: (C): b is a process_profile =Def. there is some process c such that b process_profile_of c (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [093-002])

(C) bfo-0000145.description: (C): b is a relational quality = Def. for some independent continuants c, d and for some time t: b quality_of c at t & b quality_of d at t. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [057-001])

(C) iao-0000001.description: (C): A directive information entity that specifies what should happen if the trigger condition is fulfilled.

(C) iao-0000033.description: (C): An information content entity whose concretizations indicate to their bearer how to realize them in a process.

(C) iao-0000009.description: (C): A label is a symbol that is part of some other datum and is used to either partially define  the denotation of that datum or to provide a means for identifying the datum as a member of the set of data with the same label

(C) iao-0000005.description: (C): A directive information entity that describes an intended process endpoint. When part of a plan specification the concretization is realized in a planned process in which the bearer tries to effect the world so that the process endpoint is achieved.

(C) iao-0000006.description: (C): A narrative object is an information content entity that is a set of propositions.

(C) iao-0000007.description: (C): A directive information entity that describes an action the bearer will take.

(C) iao-0000104.description: (C): A directive information entity with action specifications and objective specifications as parts that, when concretized, is realized in a process in which the bearer tries to achieve the objectives by taking the actions specified.

(C) iao-0000012.description: (C): A digital entity is an information entity which is a collection of bits that can be interpreted by a computer. Two digital entities are the same if they are bitwise identical.

(C) iao-0000013.description: (C): A report that is published in a journal.

(C) iao-0000088.description: (C): A document assembled by an author for the purpose of providing information for the audience. A report is the output of a documenting process and has the objective to be consumed by a specific audience. Topic of the report is on something that has completed. A report is not a single figure. Examples of reports are journal article, patent application, grant progress report, case report (not patient record).

(C) iao-0000311.description: (C): A document that is the output of a publishing process.

(C) iao-0000444.description: (C): A planned process of making information, such as literature, music, and software etc., available to the public for sale or for free.

(C) iao-0000015.description: (C): A quality of an information bearer that imparts the information content

(C) iao-0000017.description: (C): A model number is an information content entity specifically borne by catalogs, design specifications, advertising materials, inventory systems and similar  that is about manufactured objects of the same class. The model number is an alternative term for the class. The manufactered objects may or may not also bear the model number. Model numbers can be encoded in a variety of other information objects, such as bar codes, numerals, or patterns of dots.

(C) iao-0000019.description: (C): A binary digital entity is a digital entity that is encoded in a way that is not easily human readable and that contains other than text characters.

(C) iao-0000024.description: (C): a unit of measure is the quality of some material entity compared to which another quality is some multiple of.

(C) iao-0000025.description: (C): A language in which source code is written that is intended to be executed/run by a software interpreter. Programming languages are ways to write instructions that specify what to do, and sometimes, how to do it.

(C) iao-0000029.description: (C): A symbol that denotes a number.

(C) iao-0000031.description: (C): A numeral that denotes an integer

(C) iao-0000035.description: (C): A study interpretation is a textual entity about the implications of a study result. Examples include discussion of whether a hypothesis is false, whether the study failed to address the hypothesis, and whether the study results have led to new hypotheses

(C) iao-0000037.description: (C): A dot plot is a report graph which is a graphical representation of data where each data point is represented by a single dot placed on coordinates corresponding to data point values in particular dimensions.

(C) iao-0000038.description: (C): A diagram that presents one or more tuples of information by mapping those tuples in to a two dimensional space in a non arbitrary way.

(C) iao-0000309.description: (C): A figure that expresses one or more propositions

(C) iao-0000047.description: (C): A text based digital entity is a digital entity that is encoded so that it only contains text characters.

(C) iao-0000055.description: (C): A rule is an executable which guides, defines, restricts actions.

(C) iao-0000059.description: (C): A report figure is a report display element that has some aspect of illustration, but may be a composite of figures, images, and other elements

(C) iao-0000064.description: (C): A plan specification which describes the inputs and output of mathematical functions as well as workflow of execution for achieving an predefined objective. Algorithms are realized usually by means of implementation as computer programs for execution by automata.

(C) iao-0000065.description: (C): A software interpreter is a software application that executes some specified input software.

(C) iao-0000079.description: (C): A density plot is a report graph which is a graphical representation of data where the tint of a particular pixel corresponds to some kind of function corresponding the the amount of data points relativelly with their distance from the the pixel.

(C) iao-0000091.description: (C): A report element is a narrative object in which information is presented and consumed by a human being, and is part of a report. Examples of report elements are figure (dot plot), table, text portion (may include a movie or audio clip on a web page).

(C) iao-0000093.description: (C): Binary executable is a digital entity consisting of the binary representation of machine instructions of a specific processor or they may be binary pseudocode for a virtual machine. A non-source executable file is also called an object program. It is assumed that the binary executable file contains properly-formatted computer instructions.  (derived from Wikipedia, Nov 1, 2007)

(C) iao-0000097.description: (C): A report table is a report display element consisting of a matrix of cells layed out in a grid, some set of which are filled with some information content

(C) iao-0000098.description: (C): A data format specification is the information content borne by the document published defining the specification.  Example: The ISO document specifying what encompasses an XML document; The instructions in a XSD file

(C) iao-0000101.description: (C): An image is an affine projection to a two dimensional surface, of measurements of some quality of an entity or entities repeated at regular intervals across a spatial range, where the measurements are represented as color and luminosity on the projected on surface.

(C) iao-0000308.description: (C): An information content entity consisting of a two dimensional arrangement of information content entities such that the arrangement itself is about something.

(C) iao-0000105.description: (C): A digital document is a digital entity consisting of an electronic file which can be rendered into human-readable form by one or more computational applications.  The digital document does not refer to the information content of the document but to an instance of the file.

(C) iao-0000129.description: (C): A version number is an information content entity which is a sequence of characters borne by part of each of a class of manufactured products or its packaging and indicates its order within a set of other products having the same name.

(C) iao-0000131.description: (C): A serial number is an information content entity which is a unique sequence of characters borne by part of manufactured product or its packaging that is assigned to each individual in some class of products, and so can serve as a way to identify an individual product within the class. Serial numbers can be encoded in a variety of other information objects, such as bar codes, numerals, or patterns of dots.

(C) iao-0000132.description: (C): A lot number is an information content entity which is an identical sequence of character borne by part of manufactured product or its packaging for each instances of a product class in a discrete batch of an item. Lot numbers are usually assigned to each separate production run of an item. Manufacturing as a lot might be due to a variety of reasons, for example,  a single process during which many individuals are made from the same portion of source material. Lot numbers can be encoded in a pattern  of other information objects, such as bar codes, numerals, or patterns of dots.

(C) iao-0000140.description: (C): A settings datum is a datum that denotes some configuration of an instrument.

(C) iao-0000144.description: (C): A textual entity that expresses the results of reasoning about a problem, for instance as typically found towards the end of scientific papers.

(C) iao-0000300.description: (C): A textual entity is a part of a manifestation (FRBR sense), a generically dependent continuant whose concretizations are patterns of glyphs intended to be interpreted as words, formulas, etc.

(C) iao-0000178.description: (C): A material entity in which a concretization of an information content entity inheres.

(C) iao-0000179.description: (C): A histogram is a report graph which is a statistical description of a  distribution in terms of occurrence frequencies of different event classes.

(C) iao-0000180.description: (C): A heatmap is a report graph which is a graphical representation of data  where the values taken by a variable(s) are shown as colors in a  two-dimensional map.

(C) iao-0000181.description: (C): A Venn diagram is a report graph showing all hypothetically possible  logical relations between a finite collection of sets.

(C) iao-0000182.description: (C): A survival curve is a report graph which is a graphical representation of data where the percentage of survival is plotted as a function of time.

(C) iao-0000183.description: (C): A dendrogram is a report graph which is a tree diagram  frequently used to illustrate the arrangement of the clusters produced by a  clustering algorithm.

(C) iao-0000184.description: (C): A scatterplot is a graph which uses Cartesian coordinates to display values for two variables for a set of data. The data is displayed as a collection of points, each having the value of one variable determining the position on the horizontal axis and the value of the other variable determining the position on the vertical axis.

(C) iao-0000185.description: (C): A photograph is created by projecting an image onto a photosensitive surface such as a chemically treated plate or film, CCD receptor, etc.

(C) iao-0000186.description: (C): A photographic print is a material entity upon which a photograph generically depends.

(C) iao-0000301.description: (C): A textual entity intended to identify a particular publication.

(C) iao-0000302.description: (C): A textual entity intended to identify a particular author

(C) iao-0000590.description: (C): A textual entity that denotes a particular in reality.

(C) iao-0000303.description: (C): A textual entity intended to identify a particular institution

(C) iao-0000304.description: (C): A textual entity that describes a figure

(C) iao-0000305.description: (C): A textual entity that names a document

(C) iao-0000306.description: (C): A textual entity that contains a two-dimensional arrangement of texts repeated at regular intervals across a spatial range, such that the spatial relationships among the constituent texts expresses propositions

(C) iao-0000307.description: (C): A table where the constituent texts are abbreviations and their expansions

(C) iao-0000312.description: (C): A publication that is about an investigation

(C) obi-0000066.description: (C): a planned process that consists of parts: planning, study design execution, documentation and which produce conclusion(s).

(C) iao-0000313.description: (C): A document that has been accepted by a patent authority

(C) iao-0000314.description: (C): An information content entity that is part of a document.

(C) iao-0000315.description: (C): A summary of the entire document that is substantially smaller than the document it summarizes.  It is about the document it summarizes.

(C) iao-0000316.description: (C): A part of a publication about an investigation that is about the objective specification (why the investigation is being done)
(C) iao-0000316.label_original: introduction to a publication about an investigation

(C) iao-0000317.description: (C): A part of a publication about an investigation that is about the study design of the investigation

(C) obi-0500000.description: (C): A plan specification comprised of protocols (which may specify how and what kinds of data will be gathered) that are executed as part of an investigation and is realized during a study design execution.

(C) iao-0000318.description: (C): A part of a publication about an investigation that is about a study design execution

(C) obi-0000471.description: (C): a planned process that carries out a study design

(C) iao-0000319.description: (C): A part of a publication about an investigation that is about the study interpretation of the investigation
(C) iao-0000319.label_original: discussion section of a publication about an investigation

(C) iao-0000320.description: (C): A part of a document that has citations as parts

(C) iao-0000321.description: (C): A part of a document that enumerates the authors of the document

(C) iao-0000322.description: (C): A part of a document that has parts that are institution identifications associated with the authors of the document

(C) iao-0000323.description: (C): A part of a publication that is about the specific contributions of each author

(C) iao-0000324.description: (C): Part of a publication that is about the contributions of people or institutions other than the authors.

(C) iao-0000325.description: (C): A part of a document that is about a specific other part of the document.  Usually footnotes are spatially segregated from the rest of the document.

(C) iao-0000326.description: (C): A part of a document that is segregated from the rest of the document due to its size

(C) iao-0000327.description: (C): A table that relates document parts to specific locations in a document (usually page numbers).  This is also a document part (subsumption there should be inferred).

(C) iao-0000328.description: (C): A table that relates figures in a document to specific locations in that document (usually page numbers).  This is also a document part (subsumption there should be inferred).

(C) iao-0000329.description: (C): A shorter version of a document title

(C) iao-0000330.description: (C): A document part that describes  legal restrictions on making or distributing copies of the document

(C) iao-0000401.description: (C): A cartesion spatial coordinate datum that  uses one value to specify a position along a one dimensional spatial region
(C) iao-0000401.label_original: one dimensional cartesian spatial coordinate datum

(C) iao-0000402.description: (C): A cartesion spatial coordinate datum that  uses two values to specify a position within a two dimensional spatial region
(C) iao-0000402.label_original: two dimensional cartesian spatial coordinate datum

(C) iao-0000403.description: (C): A cartesion spatial coordinate datum that  uses three values to specify a position within a three dimensional spatial region
(C) iao-0000403.label_original: three dimensional cartesian spatial coordinate datum

(C) iao-0000408.description: (C): A scalar measurement datum that is the result of measurement of length quality

(C) iao-0000414.description: (C): A scalar measurement datum that is the result of measurement of mass quality

(C) iao-0000415.description: (C): A textual entity that expresses an assertion that is intended to be tested.

(C) iao-0000422.description: (C): A textual entity that is used as directive to deliver something to a person, or organization

(C) iao-0000442.description: (C): A role inhering in a person or organization that is realized when the bearer participates in the work which is the basis of the document, in the writing of the document, and signs it with their name.

(C) iao-0000443.description: (C): A planned process in which journal articles are read or processed and data items are extracted, typically for further analysis or indexing
(C) iao-0000443.label_original: data item extraction from journal article

(C) iao-0000445.description: (C): A document that is in preparation for submission to be published.

(C) iao-0000572.description: (C): A planned process in which a document is created or added to by including the specified input in it.

(C) iao-0000573.description: (C): A line graph is a type of graph created by connecting a series of data  points together with a line.

(C) iao-0000574.description: (C): A planned process in which a new CRID is created, associated with an entity, and stored in the CRID registry thereby registering it as being associated with some entity

(C) iao-0000575.description: (C): A planned process in which a CRID registry associates an information content entity with a CRID symbol
(C) iao-0000575.label_original: associating information with a centrally registered identifier in its registry

(C) iao-0000576.description: (C): a planned process with the objective to establish a system that allows to refer to specific entities of a certain kind and store information about them, by establishing a CRID registry and plan specifications for the process of 1) assigning a CRID and 2) looking up a CRID.

(C) iao-0000580.description: (C): A planned process in which a request to a CRID registry is made to return the information associated with a CRID symbol
(C) iao-0000580.label_original: looking up a centrally registered identifier

(C) iao-0000584.description: (C): A data set that is an aggregate of data recording some measurement at a number of time points. The time series data set is an ordered list of pairs of time measurement data and the corresponding measurement data acquired at that time.

(C) iao-0000591.description: (C): A software method (also called subroutine, subprogram, procedure, method, function, or routine) is software designed to execute a specific task.

(C) iao-0000592.description: (C): A software module is software composed of a collection of software methods.

(C) iao-0000593.description: (C): A software library is software composed of a collection of software modules and/or software methods in a form that can be statically or dynamically linked to some software application.

(C) iao-0000594.description: (C): A software application is software that can be directly executed by some processing unit.

(C) iao-0000595.description: (C): A software script is software whose instructions can be executed using a software interpreter.

(C) iao-0000605.description: (C): A textual entity listing abbreviations and their expansions that are used in a document.

(C) iao-0000606.description: (C): A part of a document where abbreviations and their long-forms used within the document are listed.

(C) iao-0000607.description: (C): A part of a document about the authors that provides biographical information and may discuss how the authors' professional experiences are relevant to the work described in the document.

(C) iao-0000608.description: (C): A textual entity expression information about an author of a document. This information may include biographical information and may discuss how the authors' professional experiences are relevant to the work described in the document.

(C) iao-0000609.description: (C): A part of a document, distinct from the abstract, that describes the significance and broader context of the document content. The author summary is often written in a non-technical manner and is aimed at both scientists and non-scientist readers.

(C) iao-0000610.description: (C): A textual entity, distinct from the abstract, that describes the significance and broader context of the document content. The author summary is often written in a non-technical manner and is aimed at both scientists and non-scientist readers, e.g as described in the article submission guidelines for PLoS Genetics (http://journals.plos.org/plosgenetics/s/submission-guidelines).

(C) iao-0000611.description: (C): A part of a document about a resource described in the document, e.g. software, that describes where and/or how that resource can be obtained.

(C) iao-0000612.description: (C): A textual entity expressing the location of a resource, e.g. software, or the manner in which a resource can be obtained.

(C) iao-0000613.description: (C): A part of a document about the medical history of a specific patient as it relates to the topic of the document.

(C) iao-0000614.description: (C): A textual entity that expresses a detailed account of a portion of the medical history for a specific patient.

(C) iao-0000615.description: (C): A part of a document used to summarize the findings discussed in the document. The conclusion section is typically found near the end of a document.

(C) iao-0000616.description: (C): A part of a document used to declare any competing interests regarding the authors and/or funding organization for the work described in the document.

(C) iao-0000617.description: (C): A textual entity that expresses a situation involving one or more of the authors, or the funding source of a document whereby the authors or funding source stand to potentially gain (typically financially) from the results reported in the document.

(C) iao-0000618.description: (C): A part of a document about the consent process that was used to enroll patients in a study.

(C) iao-0000619.description: (C): A textual entity that documents the consenting process used to enroll patients in a study.

(C) iao-0000620.description: (C): A part of a document about the governance body responsible for approving the work discussed in a document on an ethical basis.

(C) iao-0000621.description: (C): A textual entity that documents the ethical approval of some study design.

(C) iao-0000622.description: (C): A part of a document that contains one or more figures.

(C) iao-0000623.description: (C): A part of a document used to detail information regarding the source of funding used in support of the generation of the document content.

(C) iao-0000624.description: (C): A textual entity documenting the source of funding that supported some study.

(C) iao-0000625.description: (C): A part of a document detailing extensions of the described work that may be implemented at some future point in time.

(C) iao-0000626.description: (C): A textual entity expressing ideas regarding future work relevant to work described in a document that could be done.

(C) iao-0000627.description: (C): A document part announcing the publication of a novel draft genome sequence.

(C) iao-0000628.description: (C): A textual entity that describes the generation and public release of a novel, draft genome sequence.

(C) iao-0000629.description: (C): A textual entity listing keywords indicating the major theme(s) of a document.

(C) iao-0000630.description: (C): A part of a document where keywords selected by the author to categorize the major theme(s) of a document are listed.

(C) iao-0000631.description: (C): A part of a document about biases or short comings related to the study design and execution.

(C) iao-0000632.description: (C): A textual entity addressing a shortcoming or bias of a study design or execution.

(C) iao-0000633.description: (C): A part of a document about the materials required to reproduce the content of the document.

(C) iao-0000634.description: (C): A part of a document containing typically short notes about the document itself and/or the authors. Often the notes section contains subsections related to funding, competing interests, ethical approval, etc.

(C) iao-0000635.description: (C): A part of a document about the patients that participated in a study.

(C) iao-0000636.description: (C): A textual entity expressing information regarding the patients used in a study.

(C) iao-0000637.description: (C): A part of the document about the publication history of a document. This section typically details dates of document submission to a journal and dates of any re-submissions as well as reviewer comments and responses to reviewers by the authors.

(C) iao-0000638.description: (C): A textual entity that expresses the pre-publication history (submission dates, reviewer comments, etc) for a document, often including a hyperlink to a web page detailing the information.

(C) iao-0000639.description: (C): A part of a document about work in other publications that is relevant to the content of the document.

(C) iao-0000640.description: (C): A textual entity that discusses work from other publications and expresses their relevancy to the content of a document.

(C) iao-0000641.description: (C): A part of a document about a resource described in the document, e.g. software, that describes the requirements necessary to use the resource, e.g. operating systems, hardware, etc. in the case of a software resource.

(C) iao-0000642.description: (C): A textual entity that expresses the requirements necessary to use a resource, e.g. software.

(C) iao-0000643.description: (C): A textual entity documenting statistical analysis tools and techniques employed.

(C) iao-0000644.description: (C): A part of the document used to describe the statistical methodologies employed in the work presented in the document.

(C) iao-0000645.description: (C): A part of a document that contains one or more tables.

(C) iao-0000646.description: (C): An identifier that denotes some postal delivery route, some aggregate of postal delivery routes or a geographical region and was created for the purpose of sorting and delivering mail.

(C) iao-0000647.description: (C): A plan specification that if realized, is realized by the delivery of mail to some facility or mailbox within some geographical region.

(C) iao-0000648.description: (C): A postal code that is used in the United States for the purpose of sorting and delivering mail, and that denotes some postal delivery route or some aggregate of postal delivery routes.

(C) iao-0000650.description: (C): A planned process which takes as input a database and fills another database by extracting concretizations of information entities from the first, transforming them, and loading the transformed concretizations into the second.
(C) iao-0000650.label_original: database extract, transform, and load process

(C) iao-0000701.description: (C): A document part that lists and defines data variables, describes data characteristics (e.g. missing data information) and any assumptions and simplifications made.

(C) iao-0000702.description: (C): A results section that reports analyses other than main results of the study (e.g. subgroups analyses, adjusted analyses, sensitivity analyses, etc.)

(C) iao-0000703.description: (C): A document part that describes human subject(s) that participated in a study (e.g. inclusion & exclusion criteria, recruitment methods, reasons for non-participation, grouping and randomisation, methods of follow-up, etc.).

(C) iao-0000704.description: (C): A methods section that describes details of data assessment methods (data measurement).

(C) iao-0000705.description: (C): A document part that describes the physical/social/cultural conditions around a research trial.

(C) iao-0000706.description: (C): A study limitations section that describes systematic error introduced into sampling or testing by selecting or encouraging one outcome or answer over others.

(C) iao-0000707.description: (C): An abstract that is pictorial summary of the main findings described in the document.

(C) obi-0200000.description: (C): A planned process that produces output data from input data.

(OP) iao-0000135.description: (OP): c specifically denotes r =def   r is a portion of reality  & c is a particular quality  & c depends specifically on some independent continuant b   & b acquired c as the result of the achievement of an objective to enable pointing to r repeatedly.     Marked means there is a changed or additional quality of the bearer - the  quality is the information carrier.    Case 1  Memory trace as mark created when reading some description of some friend. The trace can denote.    Case 2  Pattern of ink arrayed on paper as mark when writing down a friend's name    Case 3  Pattern of magnetic domains on scattered pieces of a hard disk platter as mark when saving a file.

(OP) iao-0000142.description: (OP): An information artifact IA mentions an entity E exactly when it has a component/part that denotes E

(OP) iao-0000221.description: (OP): m is a quality measurement of q at t. When q is a quality, there is a measurement process p that has specified output m, a measurement datum, that is about q

(OP) iao-0000417.description: (OP): inverse of the relation of is quality measurement of

(OP) iao-0000413.description: (OP): relates a process to a time-measurement-datum that represents the duration of the process

(OP) iao-0000418.description: (OP): A relation between a data item and a quality of a material entity where the material entity is the specified output of a material transformation which achieves an objective specification that indicates the intended value of the specified quality.

(OP) iao-0000419.description: (OP): inverse of the relation of is quality specification of

(OP) iao-0000581.description: (OP): relates a time stamped measurement datum to the time measurement datum that denotes the time when the measurement was taken

(OP) iao-0000583.description: (OP): relates a time stamped measurement datum to the measurement datum that was measured

(OP) obi-0000293.description: (OP): A relation between a planned process and a continuant participating in that process that is not created during  the process. The presence of the continuant during the process is explicitly specified in the plan specification which the process realizes the concretization of.

(OP) ro-0000058.description: (OP): A relationship between a generically dependent continuant and a specifically dependent continuant, in which the generically dependent continuant depends on some independent continuant in virtue of the fact that the specifically dependent continuant also depends on that same independent continuant. A generically dependent continuant may be concretized as multiple specifically dependent continuants.

(OP) ro-0000059.description: (OP): A relationship between a specifically dependent continuant and a generically dependent continuant, in which the generically dependent continuant depends on some independent continuant in virtue of the fact that the specifically dependent continuant also depends on that same independent continuant. Multiple specifically dependent continuants can concretize the same generically dependent continuant.

(OP) ro-0001000.description: (OP): a relation between two distinct material entities, the new entity and the old entity, in which the new entity begins to exist when the old entity ceases to exist, and the new entity inherits the significant portion of the matter of the old entity

(OP) ro-0001001.description: (OP): a relation between two distinct material entities, the old entity and the new entity, in which the new entity begins to exist when the old entity ceases to exist, and the new entity inherits the significant portion of the matter of the old entity

(AP) iao-0000113.description: (AP): An annotation property indicating which module the terms belong to. This is currently experimental and not implemented yet.

(AP) iao-0000411.description: (AP): relates an class defined in an ontology, to the type of it's denotator

(AP) iao-0000425.description: (AP): A macro expansion tag applied to an annotation property which can be expanded into a more detailed axiom.

(AP) iao-0000426.description: (AP): An assertion that holds between an OWL Object Property and a string or literal, where the value of the string or literal is a Common Logic sentence of collection of sentences that define the Object Property.

(AP) iao-0000596.description: (AP): Relates an ontology used to record id policy to the number of digits in the URI. The URI is: the 'has ID prefix' annotation property value concatenated with an integer in the id range (left padded with '0's to make this many digits)

(AP) iao-0000597.description: (AP): Relates a datatype that encodes a range of integers to the name of the person or organization who can use those ids constructed in that range to define new terms

(AP) iao-0000598.description: (AP): Relating an ontology used to record id policy to the ontology namespace whose policy it manages

(AP) iao-0000599.description: (AP): Relates an ontology used to record id policy to a prefix concatenated with an integer in the id range (left padded with '0's to make this many digits) to construct an ID for a term being created.

(AP) iao-0000603.description: (AP): Add as annotation triples in the granting ontology

(AP) iao-0006011.description: (AP): A annotation relationship between two terms in an ontology that may refer to the same (natural) type but where more evidence is required before terms are merged.

(AP) iao-0006012.description: (AP): Used when the class or object is scheduled for obsoletion/deprecation on or after a particular date.
(AP) iao-0006012.label_original: scheduled for obsoletion on or after

(AP) iao-0000604.description: (AP): relates a class of CRID to the date after which further instances should not be made, according to the central authority

(C) ro-0002310.description: (C): A process occurring within or in the vicinity of an organism that exerts some causal influence on the organism via the interaction between an exposure stimulus and an exposure receptor. The exposure stimulus may be a process, material entity or condition (for example, lack of nutrients). The exposure receptor can be an organism, organism population or a part of an organism.

(C) ro-0002532.description: (C): Any entity that is ordered in discrete units along a linear axis.

(C) ro-0002533.description: (C): Any individual unit of a collection of like units arranged in a linear order

(C) ro-0002534.description: (C): Any entity that can be divided into parts such that each part is an atomical unit of a sequence

(OP) ro-0000300.description: (OP): OBSOLETE A relation that holds between two neurons connected directly via a synapse, or indirectly via a series of synaptically connected neurons.

(OP) ro-0000301.description: (OP): OBSOLETE A relation that holds between a neuron that is synapsed_to another neuron or a neuron that is connected indirectly to another by a chain of neurons, each synapsed_to the next, in which the direction is from the last to the first.
(OP) ro-0000301.label_original: obsolete upstream in neural circuit with

(OP) ro-0000302.description: (OP): OBSOLETE A relation that holds between a neuron that is synapsed_by another neuron or a neuron that is connected indirectly to another by a chain of neurons, each synapsed_by the next, in which the direction is from the last to the first.
(OP) ro-0000302.label_original: obsolete downstream in neural circuit with

(OP) ro-0001020.description: (OP): A relation between a material entity and a condition (a phenotype or disease) of a host, in which the material entity is not part of the host, and is considered harmless to non-allergic hosts, and the condition results in pathological processes that include an abnormally strong immune response against the material entity.

(OP) ro-0003302.description: (OP): A relationship between an entity (e.g. a genotype, genetic variation, chemical, or environmental exposure) and a condition (a phenotype or disease), where the entity has some causal or contributing role that influences the condition.

(OP) ro-0001022.description: (OP): A relation between a condition (a phenotype or disease) of a host and a material entity, in which the material entity is not part of the host, and is considered harmless to non-allergic hosts, and the condition results in pathological processes that include an abnormally strong immune response against the material entity.

(OP) ro-0001021.description: (OP): A relation between a material entity and a condition (a phenotype or disease) of a host, in which the material entity is part of the host itself, and the condition results in pathological processes that include an abnormally strong immune response against the material entity.

(OP) ro-0001023.description: (OP): A relation between a condition (a phenotype or disease) of a host and a material entity, in which the material entity is part of the host itself, and the condition results in pathological processes that include an abnormally strong immune response against the material entity.

(OP) ro-0002003.description: (OP): A relation that holds between two neurons that are electrically coupled via gap junctions.

(OP) ro-0002004.description: (OP): The relationship that holds between a trachea or tracheole and an antomical structure that is contained in (and so provides an oxygen supply to).

(OP) ro-0002009.description: (OP): A relation that applies between a cell(c) and a gene(g) , where the process of 'transcription, DNA templated (GO_0006351)' is occuring in in cell c and that process has input gene g.

(OP) ro-0002010.description: (OP): x 'regulates in other organism' y if and only if: (x is the realization of a function to exert an effect on the frequency, rate or extent of y) AND (the agents of x are produced by organism o1 and the agents of y are produced by organism o2).

(OP) ro-0002011.description: (OP): A relationship that holds between a  process that regulates a transport process and the entity transported by that process.

(OP) ro-0002313.description: (OP): Holds between p and c when p is a localization process (localization covers maintenance of localization as well as its establishment)  and the outcome of this process is to regulate the localization of c.

(OP) ro-0002012.description: (OP): A part of relation that applies only between occurrents.

(OP) ro-0002019.description: (OP): A relationship that holds between between a receptor and an chemical entity, typically a small molecule or peptide, that carries information between cells or compartments of a cell and which binds the receptor and regulates its effector function.

(OP) ro-0002020.description: (OP): Holds between p and c when p is a transport process or transporter activity and the outcome of this p is to move c from one location to another.

(OP) ro-0002026.description: (OP): A relationship that holds between two images, A and B, where:  A depicts X;  B depicts Y;  X and Y are both of type T'  C is a 2 layer image consiting of layers A and B;  A and B are aligned in C according to a shared co-ordinate framework so that common features of X and Y are co-incident with each other.  Note: A and B may be 2D or 3D.  Examples include: the relationship between two channels collected simultaneously from a confocal microscope; the relationship between an image dpeicting X and a painted annotation layer that delineates regions of X; the relationship between the tracing of a neuron on an EM stack and the co-ordinate space of the stack; the relationship between two separately collected images that have been brought into register via some image registration software.

(OP) ro-0002101.description: (OP): relationship between a neuron and a neuron projection bundle (e.g.- tract or nerve bundle) that one or more of its projections travels through.

(OP) ro-0002132.description: (OP): The relation between a neuron projection bundle and a neuron projection that is fasciculated with it.

(OP) ro-0002103.description: (OP): Relation between an anatomical structure (including cells) and a neuron that chemically synapses to it.

(OP) ro-0002120.description: (OP):  Relation between a neuron and an anatomical structure (including cells) that it chemically synapses to.

(OP) ro-0002105.description: (OP): A relation between a motor neuron and a muscle that it synapses to via a type Ib bouton.

(OP) ro-0002109.description: (OP): Relation between a muscle and a motor neuron that synapses to it via a type Ib bouton.

(OP) ro-0002106.description: (OP): A relation between a motor neuron and a muscle that it synapses to via a type Is bouton.

(OP) ro-0002112.description: (OP): Relation between a muscle and a motor neuron that synapses to it via a type Is bouton.

(OP) ro-0002107.description: (OP): A relation between a motor neuron and a muscle that it synapses to via a type II bouton.

(OP) ro-0002108.description: (OP): Relation between a muscle and a motor neuron that synapses to it via a type II bouton.

(OP) ro-0002114.description: (OP): A relation between a motor neuron and a muscle that it synapses to via a type III bouton.

(OP) ro-0002115.description: (OP): Relation between a muscle and a motor neuron that synapses to it via a type III bouton.

(OP) ro-0002121.description: (OP): Relation between a neuron and some structure  (e.g.- a brain region) in which its dendrite receives synaptic input.

(OP) ro-0002151.description: (OP): x partially overlaps y iff there exists some z such that z is part of x and z is part of y, and it is also the case that neither x is part of y or y is part of x

(OP) ro-0002156.description: (OP): d derived_by_descent_from a if d is specified by some genetic program that is sequence-inherited-from a genetic program that specifies a.

(OP) ro-0002157.description: (OP): inverse of derived by descent from

(OP) ro-0002158.description: (OP): two individual entities d1 and d2 stand in a shares_ancestor_with relation if and only if there exists some a such that d1 derived_by_descent_from a and d2 derived_by_descent_from a.

(OP) ro-0002206.description: (OP): x expressed in y if and only if there is a gene expression process (GO:0010467) that occurs in y, and one of the following holds: (i) x is a gene, and x is transcribed into a transcript as part of the gene expression process (ii) x is a transcript, and the transcription of x is part of the gene expression process (iii) x is a mature gene product such as a protein, and x was translated or otherwise processes from a transcript that was transcribed as part of this gene expression process

(OP) ro-0002214.description: (OP): x has prototype y if and only if x is an instance of C and y is a prototypical instance of C. For example, every instance of heart, both normal and abnormal is related by the has prototype relation to some instance of a 'canonical' heart, which participates in blood circulation.

(OP) ro-0002200.description: (OP): A relationship that holds between a biological entity and a phenotype. Here a phenotype is construed broadly as any kind of quality of an organism part, a collection of these qualities, or a change in quality or qualities (e.g. abnormally increased temperature). The subject of this relationship can be an organism (where the organism has the phenotype, i.e. the qualities inhere in parts of this organism), a genomic entity such as a gene or genotype (if modifications of the gene or the genotype causes the phenotype), or a condition such as a disease (such that if the condition inheres in an organism, then the organism has the phenotype).

(OP) ro-0002204.description: (OP): definition 'x has gene product of y if and only if y is a gene (SO:0000704) that participates in some gene expression process (GO:0010467) where the output of that process is either y or something that is ribosomally translated from x'

(OP) ro-0002330.description: (OP): holds between two entities when some genome-level process such as gene expression is involved. This includes transcriptional, spliceosomal events. These relations can be used between either macromolecule entities (such as regions of nucleic acid) or between their abstract informational counterparts.

(OP) ro-0002205.description: (OP): x has gene product y if and only if x is a gene (SO:0000704) that participates in some gene expression process (GO:0010467) where the output of that process is either y or something that is ribosomally translated from y

(OP) ro-0002512.description: (OP): x is the ribosomal translation of y if and only if a ribosome reads x through a series of triplet codon-amino acid adaptor activities (GO:0030533) and produces y

(OP) ro-0002510.description: (OP): x is transcribed from y if and only if x is synthesized from template y

(OP) ro-0002208.description: (OP): A parasite that kills or sterilizes its host

(OP) ro-0002217.description: (OP): OBSOLETE x actively participates in y if and only if x participates in y and x realizes some active role

(OP) ro-0002218.description: (OP): OBSOLETE x has participant y if and only if x realizes some active role that inheres in y

(OP) ro-0002227.description: (OP): A sub-relation of parasite-of in which the parasite that cannot complete its life cycle without a host.

(OP) ro-0002228.description: (OP): A sub-relations of parasite-of in which the parasite that can complete its life cycle independent of a host.

(OP) ro-0002235.description: (OP): A parasite-of relationship in which the host is a plant and the parasite that attaches to the host stem (PO:0009047)

(OP) ro-0002236.description: (OP): A parasite-of relationship in which the host is a plant and the parasite that attaches to the host root (PO:0009005)

(OP) ro-0002237.description: (OP): A sub-relation of parasite-of in which the parasite is a plant, and the parasite is parasitic under natural conditions and is also photosynthetic to some degree. Hemiparasites may just obtain water and mineral nutrients from the host plant. Many obtain at least part of their organic nutrients from the host as well.

(OP) ro-0002238.description: (OP): X 'has component participant' Y means X 'has participant' Y and there is a cardinality constraint that specifies the numbers of Ys.

(OP) ro-0002240.description: (OP): A broad relationship between an exposure event or process and any entity (e.g., an organism, organism population, or an organism part) that interacts with an exposure stimulus during the exposure event.

(OP) ro-0002244.description: (OP): Any relationship between an exposure event or process and any other entity.

(OP) ro-0002241.description: (OP): A broad relationship between an exposure event or process and any agent, stimulus, activity, or event that causes stress or tension on an organism and interacts with an exposure receptor during an exposure event.

(OP) ro-0002309.description: (OP): A relationship between an exposure event or process and any agent, stimulus, activity, or event that causally effects an organism and interacts with an exposure receptor during an exposure event.

(OP) ro-0002242.description: (OP): A broad relationship between an exposure event or process and a process by which the exposure stressor comes into contact with the exposure receptor

(OP) ro-0002243.description: (OP): A broad relationship between an exposure event or process and the course takes from the source to the target.

(OP) ro-0002245.description: (OP): g is over-expressed in t iff g is expressed in t, and the expression level of g is increased relative to some background.

(OP) ro-0002246.description: (OP): g is under-expressed in t iff g is expressed in t, and the expression level of g is decreased relative to some background.

(OP) ro-0002248.description: (OP): A relationship that holds between a substance and a chemical entity, if the chemical entity is part of the substance, and the chemical entity forms the biologically active component of the substance.

(OP) ro-0002252.description: (OP): b connecting-branch-of s iff b is connected to s, and there exists some tree-like structure t such that the mereological sum of b plus s is either the same as t or a branching-part-of t.

(OP) ro-0002291.description: (OP): x is ubiquitously expressed in y if and only if x is expressed in y, and the majority of cells in y express x

(OP) ro-0002552.description: (OP): p results in the end of s if p results in a change of state in s whereby s either ceases to exist, or s becomes functionally impaired or s has its fate committed such that it is put on a path to be degraded.

(OP) ro-0002606.description: (OP): c is a substance that treats d if c is a material entity (such as a small molecule or compound) and d is a pathological process, phenotype or disease, and c is capable of some activity that negative regulates or decreases the magnitude of d.

(OP) ro-0002303.description: (OP): x 'has habitat' y if and only if: x is an organism, y is a habitat, and y can sustain and allow the growth of a population of xs.

(OP) ro-0002325.description: (OP): a colocalizes_with b if and only if  a is transiently or peripherally associated with b[GO].

(OP) ro-0002340.description: (OP): Holds between p and c when p is a transportation or localization process and the outcome of this process is to move c to a destination that is part of some s, where the start location of c is part of the region that surrounds s.

(OP) ro-0002345.description: (OP): Holds between p and c when p is a transportation or localization process and the outcome of this process is to move c to a destination that is part of some s, where the end location of c is part of the region that surrounds s.

(OP) ro-0002348.description: (OP): p 'results in commitment to' c if and only if p is a developmental process and c is a cell and p results in the state of c changing such that is can only develop into a single cell type.

(OP) ro-0002349.description: (OP): p 'results in determination of' c if and only if p is a developmental process and c is a cell and p results in the state of c changing to be determined. Once a cell becomes determined, it becomes committed to differentiate down a particular pathway regardless of its environment.

(OP) ro-0002355.description: (OP): A relationship between a process and an anatomical entity such that the process contributes to the act of creating the structural organization of the anatomical entity.

(OP) ro-0002356.description: (OP): The relationship linking a cell and its participation in a process that results in the fate of the cell being specified. Once specification has taken place, a cell will be committed to differentiate down a specific pathway if left in its normal environment.

(OP) ro-0002357.description: (OP): p results in developmental induction of c if and only if p is a collection of cell-cell signaling processes that signal to a neighbouring tissue that is the precursor of the mature c, where the signaling results in the commitment to cell types necessary for the formation of c.

(OP) ro-0002374.description: (OP): x has_fused_element y iff: there exists some z : x has_part z, z homologous_to y, and y is a distinct element, the boundary between x and z is largely fiat

(OP) ro-0002377.description: (OP): x distributary_of y if and only if x is capable of channeling the flow of a substance to y, where y channels less of the substance than x

(OP) ro-0002378.description: (OP): x anabranch_of y if x is a distributary of y (i.e. it channels a from a larger flow from y) and x ultimately channels the flow back into y.

(OP) ro-0002382.description: (OP): x proper_distributary_of y iff x distributary_of y and x does not flow back into y

(OP) ro-0002383.description: (OP): x proper_tributary_of y iff x tributary_of y and x does not originate from y

(OP) ro-0002381.description: (OP): x main_stem_of y if y is a branching structure and x is a channel that traces a linear path through y, such that x has higher capacity than any other such path.

(OP) ro-0002400.description: (OP): p has direct input c iff c is a participant in p, c is present at the start of p, and the state of c is modified during p.

(OP) ro-0002402.description: (OP): p has direct input c iff c is a participanti n p, c is present at the end of p, and c is not present at the beginning of c.

(OP) ro-0002413.description: (OP): p provides input for q iff p is immediately causally upstream of q, and there exists some c such that p has_output c and q has_input c.

(OP) ro-0002437.description: (OP): An interaction relationship in which at least one of the partners is an organism and the other is either an organism or an abiotic entity with which the organism interacts.

(OP) ro-0002438.description: (OP): An interaction relationship in which the partners are related via a feeding relationship.

(OP) ro-0002574.label_original: participates in a biotic-biotic interaction with

(OP) ro-0002439.description: (OP): An interaction relationship involving a predation process, where the subject kills the target in order to eat it or to feed to siblings, offspring or group members

(OP) ro-0002440.description: (OP): A biotic interaction in which the two organisms live together in more or less intimate association.

(OP) ro-0002441.description: (OP): An interaction relationship between two organisms living together in more or less intimate association in a relationship in which one benefits and the other is unaffected (GO).

(OP) ro-0002442.description: (OP): An interaction relationship between two organisms living together in more or less intimate association in a relationship in which both organisms benefit from each other (GO).

(OP) ro-0002443.description: (OP): An interaction relationship between two organisms living together in more or less intimate association in a relationship in which association is disadvantageous or destructive to one of the organisms (GO).

(OP) ro-0002454.description: (OP): X 'has host' y if and only if: x is an organism, y is an organism, and x can live on the surface of or within the body of y

(OP) ro-0002446.description: (OP): A biotic interaction relationship in which one partner is an organism and the other partner is inorganic. For example, the relationship between a sponge and the substrate to which is it anchored.
(OP) ro-0002446.label_original: participates in a abiotic-biotic interaction with

(OP) ro-0002451.description: (OP): A relationship that holds between a disease and organism

(OP) ro-0002452.description: (OP): A relation that holds between a disease or an organism and a phenotype

(OP) ro-0002472.description: (OP): A relationship between a piece of evidence a and some entity b, where b is  an information content entity, material entity or process, and   the a supports either the existence of b, or the truth value of b.

(OP) ro-0002616.label_original: related via evidence or inference to

(OP) ro-0002476.description: (OP): c is a child nucleus of d if and only if c and d are both nuclei and parts of cells c' and d', where c' is derived from d' by mitosis and the genetic material in c is a copy of the generic material in d

(OP) ro-0002477.description: (OP): A child nucleus relationship in which the cells are part of a hermaphroditic organism

(OP) ro-0002478.description: (OP): A child nucleus relationship in which the cells are part of a male organism

(OP) ro-0002480.description: (OP): An interaction relation between x and y in which x catalyzes a reaction in which one or more ubiquitin groups are added to y

(OP) ro-0002583.description: (OP): holds between x and y if and only if the time point at which x starts is equivalent to the time point at which y ends. Formally: iff (x) = (y).

(OP) ro-0002593.description: (OP): holds between x and y if and only if the time point at which x ends is equivalent to the time point at which y starts. Formally: iff (x) = (y).

(OP) ro-0002505.description: (OP): p has intermediate c if and only if p has parts p1, p2 and p1 has output c, and p2 has input c

(OP) ro-0002507.description: (OP): s determined by f if and only if s is a type of system, and f is a material entity that is part of s, such that f exerts a strong causal influence on the functioning of s, and the removal of f would cause the collapse of s.

(OP) ro-0002509.description: (OP): s 'determined by part of' w if and only if there exists some f such that (1) s 'determined by' f and (2) f part_of w, or f=w.

(OP) ro-0002514.description: (OP): A relation that holds between two entities that have the property of being sequences or having sequences.

(OP) ro-0002515.description: (OP): x is sequentially adjacent to y iff x and y do not overlap and if there are no base units intervening between x and y

(OP) ro-0002527.description: (OP): x does not overlaps the sequence of x if and only if there is no z such that x has a subsequence z and z is a subsequence of y.

(OP) ro-0002516.description: (OP): x has start sequence y if the start of x is identical to the start of y, and x has y as a subsequence

(OP) ro-0002524.description: (OP): x has subsequence y iff all of the sequence parts of x are sequence parts of y

(OP) ro-0002518.description: (OP): x has end sequence y if the end of x is identical to the end of y, and x has y as a subsequence

(OP) ro-0002520.description: (OP): x is a consecutive sequence of y iff x has subsequence y, and all the parts of x are made of zero or more repetitions of y or sequences as the same type as y.

(OP) ro-0002521.description: (OP): x is sequentially aligned with if a significant portion bases of x and y correspond in terms of their base type and their relative ordering

(OP) ro-0002522.description: (OP): x bounds the sequence of y iff the upstream-most part of x is upstream of or coincident with the upstream-most part of y, and the downstream-most part of x is downstream of or coincident with the downstream-most part of y

(OP) ro-0002526.description: (OP): x overlaps the sequence of x if and only if x has a subsequence z and z is a subsequence of y.

(OP) ro-0002528.description: (OP): inverse of downstream of sequence of

(OP) ro-0002529.description: (OP): x is downstream of the sequence of y iff either (1) x and y have sequence units, and all units of x are downstream of all units of y, or (2) x and y are sequence units, and x is either immediately downstream of y, or transitively downstream of y.

(OP) ro-0002530.description: (OP): x is immediately downstream of the sequence of y iff either (1) x and y have sequence units, and all units of x are downstream of all units of y, and x is sequentially adjacent to y, or (2) x and y are sequence units, in which case the immediately downstream relation is primitive and defined by context: for DNA bases, y would be adjacent and 5' to y
(OP) ro-0002530.label_original: is immediately downstream of sequence of

(OP) ro-0002531.label_original: is immediately upstream of sequence of

(OP) ro-0002553.description: (OP): x is a hyperparasite of y iff x is a parasite of a parasite of the target organism y

(OP) ro-0002570.description: (OP): x is a conduit for y iff y overlaps through the lumen_of of x, and y has parts on either side of the lumen of x.

(OP) ro-0002573.description: (OP): A relation that holds between an attribute or a qualifier and another attribute.

(OP) ro-0002589.description: (OP): p results in catabolism of c if and only if p is a catabolic process, and the execution of p results in c being broken into smaller parts with energy being released.

(OP) ro-0002599.description: (OP): Holds between a material entity c and a pathological process p if and only if c is capable of some activity a, where a inhibits p.
(OP) ro-0002599.label_original: capable of inhibiting or preventing pathological process

(OP) ro-0002600.description: (OP): Holds between a material entity c and a pathological process p if and only if c is capable of some activity a, where a negatively regulates p.
(OP) ro-0002600.label_original: capable of upregulating or causing pathological process

(OP) ro-0002607.description: (OP): c is marker for d iff the presence or occurrence of d is correlated with the presence of occurrence of c, and the observation of c is used to infer the presence or occurrence of d. Note that this does not imply that c and d are in a direct causal relationship, as it may be the case that there is a third entity e that stands in a direct causal relationship with c and d.

(OP) ro-0002609.description: (OP): A relationship that holds between two entities, where the relationship holds based on the presence or absence of statistical dependence relationship. The entities may be statistical variables, or they may be other kinds of entities such as diseases, chemical entities or processes.

(OP) ro-0002614.description: (OP): A relationship between a piece of evidence and an entity that plays a role in supporting that evidence.

(OP) ro-0003301.description: (OP): A relation between a biological, experimental, or computational artifact and an entity it is used to study, in virtue of its replicating or approximating features of the studied entity.

(OP) ro-0002632.description: (OP): A sub-relation of parasite-of in which the parasite lives on or in the integumental system of the host

(OP) ro-0002636.description: (OP): A sub-relation of parasite-of in which the parasite is partially an endoparasite and partially an ectoparasite

(OP) ro-0002638.description: (OP): A sub-relation of endoparasite-of in which the parasite inhabits the spaces between host cells.

(OP) ro-0002640.description: (OP): A sub-relation of endoparasite-of in which the parasite inhabits host cells.

(OP) ro-0002801.description: (OP): Two or more individuals sharing the same roost site (cave, mine, tree or tree hollow, animal burrow, leaf tent, rock crack, space in man-made structure, etc.). Individuals that are sharing a communal roost may be said to be co-roosting. The roost may be either a day roost where the individuals rest during daytime hours, or a night roost where individuals roost to feed, groom, or rest in between flights and/or foraging bouts.  Communal roosting as thus defined is an umbrella term within which different specialized types -- which are not mutually exclusive -- may be recognized based on taxonomy and the temporal and spatial relationships of the individuals that are co-roosting.

(OP) ro-0008506.description: (OP): An interaction relationship describing organisms that often occur together at the same time and space or in the same environment.

(OP) ro-0003002.description: (OP): Holds between entity A (a transcription factor) and a nucleic acid B if and only if A down-regulates the expression of B. The nucleic acid can be a gene or an mRNA.

(OP) ro-0003003.description: (OP): Holds between entity A (a transcription factor) and nucleic acid B if and only if A up-regulates the expression of B. The nucleic acid can be a gene or mRNA.

(OP) ro-0003303.description: (OP): A relationship between an entity (e.g. a genotype, genetic variation, chemical, or environmental exposure) and a condition (a phenotype or disease), where the entity has some causal role for the condition.

(OP) ro-0003304.description: (OP): A relationship between an entity (e.g. a genotype, genetic variation, chemical, or environmental exposure) and a condition (a phenotype or disease), where the entity has some contributing role that influences the condition.

(OP) ro-0003305.description: (OP): A relationship between an entity (e.g. a genotype, genetic variation, chemical, or environmental exposure) and a condition (a phenotype or disease), where the entity influences the severity with which a condition manifests in an individual.

(OP) ro-0003306.description: (OP): A relationship between an entity (e.g. a genotype, genetic variation, chemical, or environmental exposure) and a condition (a phenotype or disease), where the entity influences the frequency of the condition in a population.

(OP) ro-0003307.description: (OP): A relationship between an entity (e.g. a genotype, genetic variation, chemical, or environmental exposure) and a condition (a phenotype or disease), where the presence of the entity reduces or eliminates some or all aspects of the condition.

(OP) ro-0003308.description: (OP): A relationship between an entity and a condition (phenotype or disease) with which it exhibits a statistical dependence relationship.

(OP) ro-0003309.description: (OP): A relationship between an entity (e.g. a chemical, environmental exposure, or some form of genetic variation) and a condition (a phenotype or disease), where the presence of the entity worsens some or all aspects of the condition.

(OP) ro-0003310.description: (OP): A relationship between a condition (a phenotype or disease) and an entity (e.g. a chemical, environmental exposure, or some form of genetic variation) where some or all aspects of the condition are reduced or eliminated by the presence of the entity.

(OP) ro-0003311.description: (OP): A relationship between a condition (a phenotype or disease) and an entity (e.g. a chemical, environmental exposure, or some form of genetic variation) where some or all aspects of the condition are worsened by the presence of the entity.

(OP) ro-0004001.label_original: has material basis in gain of function germline mutation in

(OP) ro-0004011.description: (OP): Relates a gene to condition, such that a mutation in this gene in a germ cell provides a new function of the corresponding product and that is sufficient to produce the condition and that can be passed on to offspring[modified from orphanet].
(OP) ro-0004011.label_original: is causal gain of function germline mutation of in

(OP) ro-0004002.label_original: has material basis in loss of function germline mutation in

(OP) ro-0004012.description: (OP): Relates a gene to condition, such that a mutation in this gene in a germ cell impairs the function of the corresponding product and that is sufficient to produce the condition and that can be passed on to offspring[modified from orphanet].
(OP) ro-0004012.label_original: is causal loss of function germline mutation of in

(OP) ro-0004003.label_original: has material basis in germline mutation in

(OP) ro-0004013.description: (OP): Relates a gene to condition, such that a mutation in this gene is sufficient to produce the condition and that can be passed on to offspring[modified from orphanet].

(OP) ro-0004004.label_original: has material basis in somatic mutation in

(OP) ro-0004014.description: (OP): Relates a gene to condition, such that a mutation in this gene is sufficient to produce the condition but that cannot be passed on to offspring[modified from orphanet].

(OP) ro-0004015.description: (OP): Relates a gene to condition, such that a mutation in this gene predisposes to the development of a condition  and that is necessary but not sufficient to develop the condition[modified from orphanet].

(OP) ro-0004006.label_original: has partial material basis in germline mutation in

(OP) ro-0004016.description: (OP): Relates a gene to condition, such that a mutation in this gene partially contributes to the presentation of this condition[modified from orphanet].
(OP) ro-0004016.label_original: is causal germline mutation partially giving rise to

(OP) ro-0004023.label_original: causal relationship with disease as subject

(OP) ro-0004020.description: (OP): A relation that holds between the disease and a material entity where the physical basis of the disease is a disorder of that material entity that affects its function.
(OP) ro-0004020.label_original: disease has basis in dysfunction of

(OP) ro-0004021.description: (OP): A relation that holds between the disease and a process where the physical basis of the disease disrupts execution of a key biological process.
(OP) ro-0004021.label_original: disease has basis in disruption of
