(OP) ro-0004022.description: (OP): A relation that holds between the disease and a feature (a phenotype or other disease) where the physical basis of the disease is the feature.

(OP) ro-0040035.description: (OP): This relation groups  relations between diseases and any other kind of entity.

(OP) ro-0004024.description: (OP): A relationship between a disease and a process where the disease process disrupts the execution of the process.

(OP) ro-0004026.description: (OP): A relationship between a disease and an anatomical entity where the disease has one or more features that are located in that entity.

(OP) ro-0004027.description: (OP): A relationship between a disease and an anatomical entity where the disease is triggered by an inflammatory response to stimuli occurring in the anatomical entity

(OP) ro-0004028.description: (OP): A relationship between a realizable entity R (e.g. function or disposition) and a material entity M where R is realized in response to a process that has an input stimulus of M.

(OP) ro-0009501.description: (OP): r 'realized in response to' s iff, r is a realizable (e.g. a plant trait such as responsivity to drought), s is an environmental stimulus (a process), and s directly causes the realization of r.

(OP) ro-0004029.description: (OP): A relationship between a disease and some feature of that disease, where the feature is either a phenotype or an isolated disease.

(OP) ro-0004030.description: (OP): A relationship between a disease and an anatomical structure where the material basis of the disease is some pathological change in the structure. Anatomical structure includes cellular and sub-cellular entities, such as chromosome and organelles.
(OP) ro-0004030.label_original: disease arises from alteration in structure

(OP) ro-0007000.description: (OP): A relation between two entities, in which one of the entities is any natural or human-influenced factor that directly or indirectly causes a change in the other entity.

(OP) ro-0007001.description: (OP): A relation between an entity and a disease of a host, in which the entity is not part of the host itself, and the condition results in pathological processes.

(OP) ro-0008501.description: (OP): An interaction relationship wherein a plant or algae is living on the outside surface of another plant.

(OP) ro-0008503.description: (OP): A sub-relation of parasite of in which a parasite steals resources from another organism, usually food or nest material

(OP) ro-0008505.description: (OP): An interaction relationship wherein one organism creates a structure or environment that is lived in by another organism.

(OP) ro-0008507.description: (OP): An interaction relationship in which organism a lays eggs on the outside surface of organism b. Organism b is neither helped nor harmed in the process of egg laying or incubation.

(OP) ro-0009001.description: (OP): 'has substance added' is a relation existing between a (physical) entity and a substance in which the entity has had the substance added to it at some point in time.

(OP) ro-0009002.description: (OP): 'has substance removed' is a relation existing between two physical entities in which the first entity has had the second entity (a substance) removed from it at some point in time.

(OP) ro-0009003.description: (OP): 'immersed in' is a relation between a (physical) entity and a fluid substance in which the entity is wholely or substantially surrounded by the substance.

(OP) ro-0009004.description: (OP): 'has consumer' is a relation between a material entity and an organism in which the former can normally be digested or otherwise absorbed by the latter without immediate or persistent ill effect.

(OP) ro-0009005.description: (OP): 'has primary substance added' indicates that an entity has had the given substance added to it in a proportion greater than any other added substance.

(OP) ro-0010001.description: (OP): A generically dependent continuant *b* generically depends on an independent continuant *c* at time *t* means: there inheres in *c* a specifically deendent continuant which concretizes *b* at *t*.

(OP) ro-0010002.description: (OP): *b* is carrier of *c* at time *t* if and only if *c* *g-depends on* *b* at *t*

(OP) ro-0011003.description: (OP): The entity A has an activity that regulates the quantity or abundance or concentration of the entity B.

(OP) ro-0011004.description: (OP): The entity A is not immediately upstream of the entity B but A has an activity that regulates an activity performed by B.

(OP) ro-0011007.description: (OP): The entity A has an activity that down-regulates by repression the quantity of B. The down-regulation is due to A having an effect on an intermediate entity (typically a DNA or mRNA element) which can produce B.    For example, protein A (transcription factor) indirectly decreases by repression the quantity of protein B (gene product) if and only if A negatively regulates the process of transcription or translation of a nucleic acid element that produces B.

(OP) ro-0011023.description: (OP): The entity A does not physically interact with the entity B, and A has an activity that down-regulates the quantity or abundance or concentration of B.

(OP) ro-0011008.description: (OP): The entity A has an activity that up-regulates by expression the quantity of B. The up-regulation is due to A having an effect on an intermediate entity (typically a DNA or mRNA element) which can produce B.    For example, protein A (transcription factor) indirectly increases by expression the quantity of protein B (gene product) if and only if A positively regulates the process of transcription or translation of a nucleic acid element that produces B.

(OP) ro-0011024.description: (OP): The entity A does not physically interact with the entity B, and A has an activity that up-regulates the quantity or abundance or concentration of B.

(OP) ro-0011009.description: (OP): The entity A has an activity that directly positively regulates the quantity of B.

(OP) ro-0011021.description: (OP): The entity A, immediately upstream of B, has an activity that directly regulates the quantity of B.

(OP) ro-0011010.description: (OP): The entity A has an activity that directly negatively regulates the quantity of B.

(OP) ro-0011013.description: (OP): The entity A is not immediately upstream of the entity B and has an activity that up-regulates an activity performed by B.

(OP) ro-0011014.description: (OP): An entity A directly interacts with B and A has an activity that decreases the amount of an entity B by degradating it.

(OP) ro-0011015.description: (OP): An entity A physically interacts with B and A has an activity that increases the amount of an entity B by stabilizing it.

(OP) ro-0011016.description: (OP): The entity A is not immediately upstream of the entity B and has an activity that down-regulates an activity performed by B.

(OP) ro-0011022.description: (OP): The entity A is not immediately upstream of the entity B, but A has an activity that regulates the quantity or abundance or concentration of B.

(OP) ro-0012000.description: (OP): a relation between a process and a continuant, in which the process is regulated by the small molecule continuant

(OP) ro-0012004.description: (OP): a relation between a continuant and a process, in which the continuant is a small molecule that regulates the process

(OP) ro-0012001.description: (OP): a relation between a process and a continuant, in which the process is activated by the small molecule continuant

(OP) ro-0012005.description: (OP): a relation between a continuant and a process, in which the continuant is a small molecule that activates the process

(OP) ro-0012002.description: (OP): a relation between a process and a continuant, in which the process is inhibited by the small molecule continuant

(OP) ro-0012006.description: (OP): a relation between a continuant and a process, in which the continuant is a small molecule that inhibits the process

(OP) ro-0012007.description: (OP): The relationship that links anatomical entities with a process that results in the adhesion of two or more entities via the non-covalent interaction of molecules expressed in, located in, and/or adjacent to, those entities.

(OP) ro-0012009.description: (OP): p is constitutively upstream of q iff p is causally upstream of q, p is required for execution of q or a part of q, and the execution of p is approximately constant.

(OP) ro-0012010.description: (OP): p removes input for q iff p is causally upstream of q, there exists some c such that p has_input c and q has_input c, p reduces the levels of c, and c is rate limiting for execution of q.

(OP) ro-0013001.description: (OP): A relationship between a neuron and a region, where the neuron has a functionally relevant number of input and/or output synapses in that region.

(OP) ro-0013002.description: (OP): A relationship between a neuron and a region, where the neuron has a functionally relevant number of input synapses in that region.

(OP) ro-0013003.description: (OP): A relationship between a neuron and a region, where the neuron has a functionally relevant number of output synapses in that region.

(OP) ro-0013004.description: (OP): A relationship between a neuron and a region, where the neuron has a functionally relevant number of input and/or output synapses distributed throughout that region (rather than confined to a subregion).

(OP) ro-0013005.description: (OP): A relationship between a neuron and a region, where the neuron has a functionally relevant number of input synapses distributed throughout that region (rather than confined to a subregion).

(OP) ro-0013006.description: (OP): A relationship between a neuron and a region, where the neuron has a functionally relevant number output synapses distributed throughout that region (rather than confined to a subregion).

(OP) ro-0013007.description: (OP): Relation between a sensory neuron and some structure in which it receives sensory input via a sensory dendrite.

(OP) ro-0013008.description: (OP): A relationship between an anatomical structure (including cells) and a neuron that has a functionally relevant number of chemical synapses to it.

(OP) ro-0013009.description: (OP): A relationship between a neuron and a cell that it has a functionally relevant number of chemical synapses to.

(OP) ro-0014001.description: (OP): A relationship between a disease and an infectious agent where the material basis of the disease is an infection with some infectious agent.

(OP) ro-0015001.description: (OP): A relation between a material entity and some data in which the data is taken as exemplifying the material entity.

(OP) ro-0015003.description: (OP): A relation between a group and another group it is part of but does not fully constitute.

(OP) ro-0015004.description: (OP): A relation that applies between a cell type and a set of markers that can be used to uniquely identify that cell type.

(OP) ro-0016002.description: (OP): A relationship that holds between an organism and a disease. Here a disease is construed broadly as a disposition to undergo pathological processes that exists in an organism because of one or more disorders in that organism.

(OP) ro-0016004.description: (OP): X has exposure medium Y if X is an exposure event (process), Y is a material entity, and the stimulus for X is transmitted or carried in Y.

(OP) ro-0018001.description: (OP): Helper relation for OWL definition of RO:0018002 myristoylates

(OP) ro-0018002.description: (OP): A molecularly-interacts-with relationship between two entities, where the subject catalyzes a myristoylation activity that takes the object as input

(OP) ro-0018027.description: (OP): a relation between a ligand (material entity) and a receptor (material entity) that implies the binding of the ligand to the receptor activates some activity of the receptor

(OP) ro-0018028.description: (OP): a relation between a ligand (material entity) and a receptor (material entity) that implies the binding of the ligand to the receptor inhibits some activity of the receptor to below basal level

(OP) ro-0018029.description: (OP): a relation between a ligand (material entity) and a receptor (material entity) that implies the binding of the ligand to the receptor reduces some activity of the receptor to basal level

(OP) ro-0019501.description: (OP): Relates a gene to condition, such that a variation in this gene predisposes to the development of a condition.

(DP) ro-0002029.description: (DP): Then percentage of organisms in a population that die during some specified age range (age-specific mortality rate), minus the percentage that die in during the same age range in a wild-type population.

(AP) ro-0002422.description: (AP): Used to annotate object properties to describe a logical meta-property or characteristic of the object property.
(AP) ro-0002422.label_original: logical macro assertion on an object property

(AP) ro-0002172.description: (AP): An assertion that holds between an ontology class and an organism taxon class, which is intepreted to yield some relationship between instances of the ontology class and the taxon.

(AP) ro-0002420.description: (AP): A logical macro assertion whose domain is an IRI for a class
(AP) ro-0002420.label_original: logical macro assertion on a class

(AP) ro-0002173.description: (AP): S ambiguous_for_taxon T if the class S does not have a clear referent in taxon T. An example would be the class 'manual digit 1', which encompasses a homology hypotheses that is accepted for some species (e.g. human and mouse), but does not have a clear referent in Aves - the referent is dependent on the hypothesis embraced, and also on the ontogenetic stage.  [PHENOSCPAE:asilomar_mtg]

(AP) ro-0002416.description: (AP): An assertion that involves at least one OWL object that is intended to be expanded into one or more logical axioms. The logical expansion can yield axioms expressed using any formal logical system, including, but not limited to OWL2-DL.

(AP) ro-0002419.description: (AP): An assertion that holds between an OWL Annotation Property P and a non-negative integer N, with the interpretation: for any P(i j) it must be the case that | { k : P(i k) } | = N.

(AP) ro-0002423.label_original: logical macro assertion on an annotation property

(AP) ro-0002421.description: (AP): A logical macro assertion whose domain is an IRI for a property
(AP) ro-0002421.label_original: logical macro assertion on a property

(AP) ro-0002474.description: (AP): An assertion that holds between an OWL Object Property and a dispositional interpretation that elucidates how OWL Class Axioms or OWL Individuals that use this property are to be interpreted in a dispositional context. For example,  A binds B may be interpreted as A have a mutual disposition that is realized by binding to the other one.

(AP) ro-0002484.description: (AP): Connects an ontology entity (class, property, etc) to a URL from which curator guidance can be obtained. This assertion is inherited in the same manner as functional annotations (e.g. for GO, over SubClassOf and part_of)

(AP) ro-0002504.description: (AP): S always_present_in_taxon T if every fully formed member of taxon T has part some S, or is an instance of S

(AP) ro-0002535.label_original: temporal logical macro assertion on a class

(AP) ro-0002539.description: (AP): Count of number of days intervening between the start of the stage and the time of fertilization according to a reference model. Note that the first day of development has the value of 0 for this property.

(AP) ro-0002540.description: (AP): Count of number of days intervening between the end of the stage and the time of fertilization according to a reference model. Note that the first day of development has the value of 1 for this property.

(AP) ro-0002541.description: (AP): Count of number of years intervening between the start of the stage and the time of birth according to a reference model. Note that the first year of post-birth development has the value of 0 for this property, and the period during which the child is one year old has the value 1.

(AP) ro-0002542.description: (AP): Count of number of years intervening between the end of the stage and the time of birth according to a reference model. Note that the first year of post-birth development has the value of 1 for this property, and the period during which the child is one year old has the value 2

(AP) ro-0002543.description: (AP): Count of number of months intervening between the start of the stage and the time of birth according to a reference model. Note that the first month of post-birth development has the value of 0 for this property, and the period during which the child is one month old has the value 1.

(AP) ro-0002544.description: (AP): Count of number of months intervening between the end of the stage and the time of birth according to a reference model. Note that the first month of post-birth development has the value of 1 for this property, and the period during which the child is one month old has the value 2

(AP) ro-0002545.description: (AP): Defines the start and end of a stage with a duration of 1 month, relative to either the time of fertilization or last menstrual period of the mother (to be clarified), counting from one, in terms of a reference model. Thus if month_of_gestation=3, then the stage is 2 month in.

(AP) ro-0002546.description: (AP): A relationship between a stage class and an anatomical structure or developmental process class, in which the stage is characterized by the appearance of the structure or the occurrence of the biological process

(AP) ro-0002547.description: (AP): Count of number of days intervening between the start of the stage and the time of coitum.

(AP) ro-0002548.description: (AP): Count of number of days intervening between the end of the stage and the time of coitum.

(AP) ro-0002560.description: (AP): If Rel is the relational form of a process Pr, then it follow that: Rel(x,y) <-> exists p : Pr(p), x subject-partner-in p, y object-partner-in p
(AP) ro-0002560.label_original: is asymmetric relational form of process class

(AP) ro-0002562.description: (AP): R is the relational form of a process if and only if either (1) R is the symmetric relational form of a process or (2) R is the asymmetric relational form of a process
(AP) ro-0002562.label_original: is relational form of process class

(AP) ro-0002561.description: (AP): If Rel is the relational form of a process Pr, then it follow that: Rel(x,y) <-> exists p : Pr(p), x partner-in p, y partner-in p
(AP) ro-0002561.label_original: is symmetric relational form of process class

(AP) ro-0002594.description: (AP): An annotation property that connects an object property to a class, where the object property is derived from or a shortcut property for the class. The exact semantics of this annotation may vary on a case by case basis.
(AP) ro-0002594.label_original: is relational form of a class

(AP) ro-0002580.label_original: logical macro assertion on an axiom

(AP) ro-0002601.description: (AP): A shortcut relationship that holds between two entities based on their identity criteria
